$n, you come with me.
Yes... Very good. Around Shadowmoon Valley are four arkonite crystals, ancient wreckage from our vessel.
I thought we would never need their power, but the time has come. Take my staff, and gather their energy for me.
All right, give me one moment...
There are still enemies among us. EVERYONE TO ARMS!
You must defeat Commander Vorka. There he is, at the very gates of Karabor.
With pleasure. Vindicators, follow me into the fray!
Furious little orcling!
In your blind rage you rush to face my ogres alone.
They will end you, little lone wolf.
Your conquered clan will fill my slave pens...
I'll drown you in the blood of your little army!
I will get these orcs to safety and meet with you outside.
Get me lose and I will speak with your wolf chief.
Let's go.
Text1: Let's go.

Text: I... feel... better! You've done the right thing! Now I shall go see what your wolf chief has to say.
The siege is broken! Come, brothers and sisters - drive these orcs from Karabor!
Karabor stands, for today.
You will not die today, champion!
Text1: You will not die today, champion!

Text: Let the Light heal your wounds!
Text1: Let the Light heal your wounds!

Text: The Light protects its champions.
Text1: The Light protects its champions.

Text: Thank you, $n. I will meet you back at Twilight Glade.
Text1: Thank you, $n. I will meet you back at Twilight Glade.

Text: Look! Fire!
Text1: Look! Fire!

Text: Aaauuughh!
Text1: Aaauuughh!

Text: No, Ga'nar. We are surrounded and exposed. We must fortify.
Reckless brother!
O're atal'sha! For the Light!
Text1: O're atal'sha! For the Light!

Text: We will not yield!
Text1: We will not yield!

Text: Forward! For Karabor!
Text1: Forward! For Karabor!

Text: There is much to be done. Taalo, see that the troops are healed and rested.

Text1: Gah! He tried to stab me! I told you we couldn't trust the Laughing Skulls.

Text: Limbflayer forgot to be nice. I saw pretty orc. I wanted to see if she could dance. Sorry. Sorry.
I have come to hunt the Iron Horde. I could destroy what remains of your ruined village, or perhaps we could assist one another.
Yes, wolves and skulls need each other. You need to know where the big Iron Hordy weapon is at. We need your $p.
You have proven yourself loyal to my clan. Capable of great things.
Our hold on Bladespire is tenuous, and some of my best warriors have raced off with my reckless brother.
I was impressed by your skill in our battle against Dorogg the Ruthless.
I would be honored if you continued to fight by our side.
I will block the temple against any more damage.
Go, $n. I will hold the temple gates!
Look out!

Text1: Fan out! Leave nothing alive!

Text: Let's get movin', then!
Lemme just get her warmed up...
Come on, baby girl...
There we go!
This way. There is a safe spot up ahead, just outside the Iron Horde's facilities.
I s'pose priority number one is to take care o' that nasty giant cannon.
Did somebody say "giant cannon"?
Soon enough. Our first priority is to find Yrel. She is out there somewhere.
D'kaan, you and our champion did some scouting earlier. What did you find?
...nothing conclusive, Vindicator.
I see. Well then, we will just have to...
I'll dispatch artificers to secure the crystals to the north.
And what of Ner'zhul? Will we let him take our people without retribution?
Patience, Maraad. A rescue will require planning - do not rush into danger until we know where our people are.
We made the wrong choice once before. I won't let it happen again. I can't leave our people to die.

Text1: I will keep an eye on him, teacher.
When the Iron Horde came, they gave our clan a choice. Join them, or die.
My husband Ner'zhul chose to save our people. He joined the Iron Horde, but they asked of him a heavy price.
They said:
So Ner'zhul turned to the silent void. He broke the ancient laws, and drew upon the dark star.
I pleaded with him to stop, but he would not turn back.
By breaking this stone, he forswore all loyalty to our ancestors.
I can ask only one thing of you now, stranger.
You must do what I cannot. Stop Ner'zhul. End his madness before it is too late.
Good work, $p! Meet us at the rendezvous. Time to see how to drive this beast.

Text: What good are stars and visions against steel and powder? Make a worthy offering, or your people shall die.

Text1: The Shadowmoon fortress is sealed to outsiders, but this keystone will allow entry. Good luck, hero.

Text: Ner'zhul! Your army is scattered, your fortress in ruins.
Your "dark star" has fallen, and now serves the draenei. You are a disgrace!
We would still serve the Iron Horde, Hellscream. Our magic is-
YOU HAVE NO PLACE IN MY IRON HORDE! Go back to your little village, Ner'zhul.  You can watch the stars while the Iron Tide washes over you.
Go back to your little village, Ner'zhul.  You can watch the stars while the Iron Tide washes over you.
Korhol, Zhakta, Trokar... move in from all sides. Gargrak, hold for now.
ZHAKTA NO!... you will be avenged!
Dammit all. Gargrak, go now... kill the blind shaman.
RETREAT! WE'LL BE BACK, FROSTWOLVES!
Kalandrios, I would like to witness the Ritual of Binding again.
Text1: Kalandrios, I would like to witness the Ritual of Binding again.
Sorcerous coward.

Text: The Iron Horde are moving toward the Temple of Karabor. The attack has beg--
Wait... what is that light?
Stand back!
It seems the elements of Draenor do not respond to me as they do on Azeroth...
Go on ahead. Durotan awaits. I must catch my breath.
To Bladespire! Attack!
There is no time to waste! We strike NOW!
Dorogg has fallen! Stay close, Frostwolves - the citadel is not yet ours.
Press the attack!
The Frostwolves will triumph.
This fortress will fall.
Do not give up!
Gather your strength!
Carry the light, brothers and sisters!
That was barely a scratch! I should recover quickly.
It is up to you, champion. I will stay here and help with the wounded slaves you rescued.

Text1: Nothing worthwhile ever is.

Text: Drek'Thar, old friend, you're alive!
I know your eyes don't work, shaman, but this one has green skin.
Hmph. Yes. Ga'nar is already causing trouble.
Very well, strangers. You have earned the trust of our shaman. I will not turn away the help.
I can barely stand. But for the actions of these heroes, I would be dead.
These are champions from a faraway realm, pledged to fight the Iron Horde.
I do not need eyes to see it; they are noble of heart. They saved our kin -- including your brother.
Come, friends. If you wish to fight with our clan, we welcome you to receive our blessings.
Reach out to the Shamanstone. Embrace the wisdom of this land and the ancestors that came before us.
Warriors! Today the tide turns.
We will claim Bladespire Citadel as our own.
Fight as one. We win this - together!
Ga'nar is a great fighter, but he is impatient. He has taken some of our best warriors with him.
He never listens. His ruthlessness may cost us.
Here - Gormaul Tower. This will be our foothold. Leave none alive! LOK'TAR OGAR!
The Bladespire ogres threw me into that hellhole. I'll notch my axe with their skulls until vengeance is mine!
Bladespire Citadel! I will have my vengeance on those ogres, even if I have to tear it down stone by stone.
My friends, you have earned a hero's welcome. Follow us to the Frostwolf Chieftain.
My eyes may not work, but the familiar chill of the air is comforting.
Ah yes. Garad's youngest: a noble soul named Durotan.
Wise beyond his years, but still young. I fear he has been thrust into the Gronn's jaws - our people are in great danger.
You mentioned the Frostwolf Chieftain...
Durotan!

Text1: Fomic ore is tougher than hardened steel. You will need my goren-toothed pick axe to cut through the rock.
The spirits were kind to guide you to me at this moment.
It is done! The blade is forged.
You now stand before Na'Shra! Weaponsmith of the Frostwolf Clan. For your service, I give you mine.

Text: You are hurt. Your flesh is pale.
The battle is joined. Lok-Narash!
Reinforcements approach. Attack!
The stench of a boar beast. Beware its tusks... Charge!
The tower is ours! Regroup and press on!
I will ride ahead. Frostwolves, hold the tower. Igrimar, with me!
I will forestall any counterattacks by the enemy. Lok'tar ogar!
Stand down, Warlord. It is over.
...Fenris?
No slave fights with the will of one who is free.
The Thunderlords retreat! They are making their way through Thunder Pass to the Iron Horde.
They are going to retaliate. We must be ready.
What is this...?
No, I will never be okay with this.
Come! To Thunder Pass. We are outnumbered 50 to 1. They don't stand a chance!
Thank you, child. I can always count on you.
There! Is this what you seek, Prophet?

Text1: Kron approaches! Champion, with me.

Text: If I try to release Exurotus it is sure to bring Kron down on us.
We have company, Master.
Tagar, deal with the intruder.
Frostwolves! The Iron Horde is coming. As we speak, they march on Thunder Pass.
But the Frostwolf clan is reunited! Together, we can protect this land!
Lok-Narash, Frostwolves! Prepare for battle!
You know me, brother. I'm always ready to fight.
Hold your position, Frostwolves! Let them come to you!
Axes up! Here they come again!
We can't fight with this cannon fire coming down. Thrall! $p! Take care of that tank!
Drek'Thar's in trouble. Ga'nar, get out there and lend him a hand.
You go too, $p.  Make sure my brother doesn't get himself killed.
Fall back! Prepare for the next attack!
Spears incoming! Hold your ground!
Hero, approach my totem for aid!
I'll be waiting.
Frostwolves! Stand strong! The battle is nearly done!
Drek'Thar! How much time do you need?
We are counting on you, shaman!
I do. Something big is coming.
GRONN!
All Frostwolves - charge ahead! Take that thing down!
Draka, make your way to the cave the scout spotted. I will meet the commander at the coastal village.
Champion, we will meet you ahead when you are done with your mission.

Text1: Lead it away from Drek'Thar!

Text: Exurotus is too weak. The most I can do is free him of his bonds. Death will claim him shortly afterward.
If I were stronger...

Text1: There must be something you can do.

Text: The fury is dying. We don't have much time.
There might be something. Exurotus, I offer my spirit as host to your own. Join with me, so that your fire may not be quenched.
MY SPIRIT... BURNS!

Text1: Drek'Thar, what has it done to you?

Text: He has become one with the fury. Their spirits are now merged.
I... I can see. I can see the shift of the elements, the movement of the spirits through the land. It is glorious.
The ogres will suffer for what they've done!
We will secure our borders!
Text1: We will secure our borders!

Text: Flowers?! Noooooo!
Please... no flowers...
Not me! Not now!
Not like this...
The legends are true!
Anything but flowers!
Flowers?

Text1: So the wolves have come to play with the skulls? I will speak with Durotan but I will not hold out hope. His wolves are soft and lack conviction.

Text: Ahhh!!!!! Finish it! Just let me die!
No excuses, Kor'gall. We are at WAR with another world. Motivate your people, get a mining pick yourself, I do not care. You WILL meet your quota or find your clan the target of our next weapon test.
Here, let me make some adjustments.
There ya go.
Durotan? Draka? What are YOU doing here?
Orgrim Doomhammer! You will be made to answer for your attack on my people!
Stay your hand, hero. I want him alive.
I have not forgotten or forgiven that. But Orgrim was once an honorable orc, and my closest friend. I owe it to him to at least try to help him regain some of his honor.
Always sentimental, Durotan. I am as loyal to my people as you are to yours. Do not presume that I walk this path willingly. Some things are more important than honor.

Text1: Husband? It was his forces that killed your brother.

Text: So much for subtlety. Those Laughing Skull are going to get us all killed.
Hmph. I remember ogre architecture being more formidable.
I issued no such order. I wanted your people to join us and protect this world from the threat of those beyond the portal.
You are my vanguard.
These shores are ours!
Leave no enemy alive!
Iron will, iron blood.
Go forth to victory!
Not long ago, we were orcs of many clans, quibbling over scraps in a world that was ours for the taking.
Now, as one clan, no enemy can hope to stand against the Iron Horde!
We will crush their bones beneath our boots.  We will burn their cities to ash!
The iron tide washes over them!
The doom that is coming will destroy us all. These outsiders will bring a wave of fire and death down upon us if the orcs do not act as one to destroy them first.

Because I have witnessed it! Every night! Every night for many months now. My dreams become nightmares, and in those nightmares I watch helplessly as the land corrupts beneath our feet and the sky is turned to fire.
Say what you will, but this is the doom that is coming. And it is these creatures from beyond the portal that will bring it.
And how can you be so certain of such a fate?

Text1: I have never known the great Doomhammer to be afraid of anything.

Text: Cho'gall! I sent you here to enslave this thing.

Text1: Yes! Let us free ALL of the skulls! Remind them how to laugh! Burn all of the slavers to ash and ruin!

Text: SKULLS!
Text1: SKULLS!

Text: Aaaaaaaaaaahhhhhhhh! Ha ha ha!
Fire! Fire! Waa-aaaaaa! Ha!
Hero, meet us at Twilight Glade. We must save the prisoners.

Text1: Burn burn burn burn torch and burn and cinder and burn and FIRE!

Text: Thank you, champion. I have always felt my fate and that of the Dark Star are intertwined.
Light. Pure light. Hope in times of despair, brightness in our darkest hour!
Ner'zhul's ritual... begins! We are out of time!
We must stop the Shadowmoon Chieftain.
What needs to be done, child.
Hurry, champion. I will get there as soon as I can.
Do whatever you can to delay Ner'zhul...

Text1: Prophet! What have you done to yourself!?

Text: LAUGHING SKULL! LAUGHING SKULL! HAHAHAHAHA!

Text1: LAUGHING SKULL! LAUGHING SKULL! HAHAHAHAHA!

Text: This forest is ours!
Yrel! We will spill some orcish blood...
I am your Chieftain; you and your warriors will fall back in line.
OUR - FATHER - would BE - ASHAMED - of WHAT - YOU'VE - BECOME!
Our strength comes from working together.
[PH] Temporary cut-scene with my brother? Let's do it!
Yrel, walk with us a moment...
I... already told you... all that I know...
The Iron Horde will not hesitate to use that cannon on our base. We should find a more tactical location.
Is everyone alright?
I think I soiled m'self...
My ALE was back there...
Yes, everyone appears to be alright.
Very well. We will set up camp ahead, and deal with this cannon.
Yrel will have to wait.
Everybody in the Tank. Yrel is being held as a slave in the Stonemaul ogres' slave camp.
Yrel might already be free if it weren't for the actions of one deceitful rangari.
I did what I thought was right, Vindicator. The missing girl seems to be distracting you from our mission.
Yeah, what's so special about this girl anyway?
I lost her once. I will not lose her again.
Now THAT'S somethin' I can get behind.
Besides, the ogres're sellin' slaves to the Iron Horde. Stoppin' ta beat 'em up fer a bit is well within the scope o' our mission.
You all is gonna get smashed.
Oh no, ogre, that's where you have it wrong. You see, we are the ones that will be doing the smashing today. Thaelin?
Aye aye, cap'n!
Now is our chance! Forward, Thaelin, with speed!
What da...?
Stay silent, all of you! Ogre, if you so much as GRUNT, I will personally beat the Light out of you.
We can set up over there.
Ok'mokk didn't make no sounds at all. You don' need ta smash Ok'mokk.
Ach, I have a feelin' yer gonna get smashed anyway.
A direct attack. A bold decision.
Gathering allies. Wise decision.
Form up, everyone. We are headed to Smokebelcher Depot.
Form up, everyone. We are headed to the Planteau. [TEMP NAME]

Text1: Room for one more on that elekk?

Text: Always, my love.
Yrel, did you learn anything about the Goliath Cannon before your capture?

Text1: A bit. The one you destroyed was merely a prototype. The actual cannons are built in the foundry, to the north.
I overheard one of the orcish leaders discussing a plan to use them on Shattrath.

Text: Shattrath? Ha! Even that big ol' hunk o' metal couldn't hit Shattrath from here.
They could if it was loaded onta' a boat.
I suspected the same thing. They must plan to load the cannons onto barges at the Naval Base, in the northeast.
Our small group would never survive an attack on the Naval Base. Too fortified.
We will continue attacking their supply lines.

Text1: D'kaan, how long have you been scouting out here in Gorgrond?

Text: A very long time. Longer than you've been alive, probably by two or threefold.
D'ye get lonely?
A rangari who is not lonely is not doing his job.
Sounds like a crap job to me. Life ain't worth livin' if y'don't have lads and a lass t'come home to.

Text1: Do you have a wife, Hansel?

Text: Ach... the Blackrocks took 'er away.
That's half o'why I'm here: ta look after Thaelin, and ta get me wife back.
We will find your wife, Hansel. And we will leave a wake of bodies behind us. The orcs will pay with blood for what they did to our families.
Y'know, that's the darkest, coldest, most inspirin' thing I've ever heard from the lips of a paladin.
Our work here is done. Next, we head to Smokebelcher Depot.
Our work here is done. Next, we head to the Planteau.

Text1: Thaelin, are you doing alright in there?

Text: Quite fine, ma'am. Just happy to be out o' combat and back in me Tank.

Text1: <sigh> This land is plagued by war. Do you think you'll return to the safety of home after our mission is done?

Text: I dunno how much you've heard about Azeroth, ma'am, but we've got our fair share of war, too.
Once I've found me Ellie, I know I'll be headed back ta Searin' Gorge.
What about you, lassie? Will ye go home?

Text1: With Velen gone, I feel like I don't have a home anymore.

Text: We are draenei, Yrel. Being without a home is in our nature.

Text1: I was thinking I might go through the portal with you, my love.

Text: Yes, Yrel. You will have a home on Azeroth.
But first, we will make these orcs suffer for what they did to you. Their sins cannot be forgiven.

Text1: Maraad, you're frightening me.

Text: The Iron Horde's supply lines are now cut, however temporarily. We have forged our alliance with the Shapers.
There will never be a better time than this. Let us head to the Naval Base and exact our vengeance on the Iron Horde!

Text1: What is our plan, Maraad?

Text: We will slay as many of the vile things as we can. We will burn their homes and show them fear.
I will make them feel the pain I felt when I lost you, Yrel.

Text1: Maraad... I am honored...
...but perhaps you are taking your vengeance too far. Have you forgotten what the Prophet taught us?

Text: The prophet is DEAD, Yrel. Look what his teachings did for him.
Ye've gone too far, Maraad.
The Light's left ye. Even I can see that.
I carry no particular love for the Light, but I agree. You need to remember what you stand for, Vindicator.
Are any of you more holy than me? I am the LEADER of this expedition, and I will not be questioned any further!
The Light has not left me, Thaelin. No... the Light has finally shown me its true form.
Vengeance.
I saw the naaru's vengeance in the Purge of Grommar. I was there as K'ara herself unleashed holy death upon the filthy hordes.
[UNUSED]

Text1: Maraad, my love. That's enough.

Text: Yrel...

Text1: You have been through too much, Maraad. Your thirst for vengeance will only lead to our death.
[UNUSED]
Rest now. I will lead our attack on the Naval Base.

Text: I'm with you, Yrel.
I, too, will follow you.
And I.
Very well.
Thank you, Yrel. I don't know what's coming over me.
It is no matter. These souls are mine. My power grows.
Auchindoun will be mine! I will devour every last soul and bathe the ashes in hellfire!

Text1: Yes, Tuulani. Now you see.
Your efforts were valiant. I did not think the anchorites could power the defenses with only one of the crystals.
But nothing will stop my plan, nor that of my masters. And the only things in our way...
Protector! Destroy these intruders!

Text: Run for your lives!
Text1: Run for your lives!

Text: Wow! Thanks! I can find my way out of here now. I'm sure I won't get captured again. See ya!
I fear that even with the Heart intact, Auchindoun's defenses may not be enough. The Shadow Council has eyes everywhere.

Text1: Mother?
Confound these wards! No matter how much I call upon the light to purge them it is as if the wards themselves thwart my ability to unmake them.

Text: The runes have been destroyed.
Text1: The runes have been destroyed.

Text: Ready to face Revaan?
Text1: Ready to face Revaan?

Text: Child! Leave now. Those wards were there for your protection. You should not be here.
Yes. And she will never be yours.

Text1: Tuulani, go to Telmor and meet with Soulbinder Aedraa. She has retrieved the final fragment and brought it there.
Right away.

Text: De slaves are ready for ye boss.
Good, their wretched spirits will serve me better than their weak bodies ever could!
Hush, you idiot!
Ahhhh... Yes, now the Soulgrinder hums with power! With this, we shall be unstoppable!

Text1: Looks like there's only one way out, hero. UP!

Text: You do not understand the Great Work.
You cannot defy the Great Work.
This is the way of things. You cannot stop it.
You do not understand... You cannot know...
Yay! We unstoppable! We unstoppable!
I must return to the spirit world to continue my research. Guard this room and make sure that NO ONE touches the portal!
Come forth, Soulgrinder! Devour the souls that we have brought for you!
Axes down, brothers! Don't you recognize your own clan?
We are home.

Text1: What do you make of it, Thrall?

Text: It reeks of hatred and dust, Choluna. I don't like having it here at the garrison.
I'd like it even less in the hands of the Iron Horde.
We should destroy it.
Perhaps. First, we must find out what purpose it serves for Blackhand.
Choluna, step up our operation in Gorgrond. Whatever the Iron Horde are planning, I want to be ready.
And what are you supposed to be?
Amazing.
This is Frostwolf territory, but you may claim this plateau as your own. Consider it a reward for rescuing my people.
Thank you, chieftain. We will establish a foothold immediately.
Even our wyverns are not prepared for this type of cold.
Text1: Even our wyverns are not prepared for this type of cold.

Text: It looks as though we will not have allies in the skies for this one.
Text1: It looks as though we will not have allies in the skies for this one.

Text: We are going to have to find a better way to shield our wyvern from the cold.
Text1: We are going to have to find a better way to shield our wyvern from the cold.

Text: It would seem we need to rely on the local rylak for air travel.
Text1: It would seem we need to rely on the local rylak for air travel.

Text: Nope.
What do you make of it, Yrel?

Text1: It reeks of hatred and dust, Omnuron. I don't like this.

Text: We should destroy it.
This terrain is ideal for a stronghold.
I can open up a portal to Orgrimmar only briefly. Reinforcements are standing by, I hope?
The very best.
Somebody call for a fixer?
... You're entrusting a goblin to be your foreman?
Gazlowe, here, oversaw the construction of Orgrimmar.
Orgrimmar! The impenetrable fortress!
Wasn't it recently sacked?
Yeah yeah, okay, one little sacking.
Omnuron, step up our operation in Gorgrond. Whatever the Iron Horde are planning, I want to be ready.
What is this -- Wise-ear! You are alive!
Lead us to Durotan, old friend.
Wor'gol is the winter home of the Frostwolf Clan.
Durotan walks a cliff's edge, pinned between the Thunderlord orcs and Bladespire ogres.
Ga'nar seemed bent on dealing out retribution to both.
Ah yes! I worry about Durotan's brother. Always quick to fight. His need for vengeance will make him more reckless than ever.
What is THAT? I see a fortress of stone!
Bladespire Citadel. Once a far-flung outpost of the ogre empire.
If our people are to have any hope to survive, we must rout the ogres from their stronghold.
This is Durotan's goal. He will not ask for it, but we will need your help!

Text1: Ga'nar did not wait for the muster call. His blood burns too hot.
Go! Win us a great victory. Tell my husband I will defend the town until he returns.
The Legion won't give up so easily. Auchindoun is too valuable to them.
Teron'gor! The Light comes for you!

Text: The Legion will not stop here. They desire Auchindoun too much.
Nyami. Tuulani. We ride for Light's Rest immediately.
The vanguard is falling. We will not let their great sacrifice be in vain!
Your sacrifices will not be forgotten, Netherwane.
Archmage, let me stay behind. It was my sworn duty to watch over this portal.
I shared that duty with you, Dar'toon.  We will meet the enemy together.
They will sing songs of your heroism, Dar'toon.
Just get me free, stranger. I could kill a hundred of these pigs with this shovel alone.
Prepare to heroically CTRL-E through the portal with me!

Text1: I'll lead the wounded to safety. Cover our escape!

Text: Whoever you are... thank you.
Text1: Whoever you are... thank you.

Text: They were bleeding us dry. I don't think we had much longer...
Text1: They were bleeding us dry. I don't think we had much longer...

Text: Whoever you are... thank you.
Text1: Whoever you are... thank you.

Text: They were bleeding us dry. I don't think we had much longer...
Text1: They were bleeding us dry. I don't think we had much longer...

Text: Help us!
Text1: Help us!

Text: Set us free!
Text1: Set us free!

Text: Is anybody out there?
Text1: Is anybody out there?

Text: Help! Anybody!
Text1: Help! Anybody!
$p, I think you should follow Tuulani and protect her. We need to ensure the crystal reaches Auchindoun safely.

Text: $p, you should follow Tuulani and protect her. We must ensure the crystal reaches Auchindoun safely.
Blessings to you, stranger. Because of you, I will see daylight once more.

Text1: Thank you, stranger! I was supposed to be their next meal...
Thank you, hero. I can fight my way out of here on my own.

Text: We must deny Teron'gor entrance to Auchindoun. Come, let us meet at Retribution Point and discuss how to bring the fight to the enemy.
You have *cough* restored this dying orc's honor, champion. Farewell. And farewell, Snowpaw, my old friend...

Text1: Thank you, hero. Your deeds will be remembered.

Text: I've seen enough here.
Kargath, you coward!
You wouldn't last ten seconds against me, draenei.
You sound afraid, Kargath.
Two on one? Now, you speak my language!
That's not very sportsmanlike, Bladefist. Why don't we settle this in the arena?
Hold everything! Now, they speak my language!
But I'm afraid you're not much more than a warm-up, draenei. Doesn't anyone else feel like dying today?
Thought you'd never ask.
Return to Khadgar, champion! We will buy you the time you need!
I feel the flames dying down. What is happening, exarch?
We have a visitor. Perhaps... a savior.
We are freed! Follow me, shaman. We will escape through the hills.
He is right. The Iron Horde will move against us. We must be ready.
No, I will never be okay with this.
He made his choice.
You take care of the lieutenants, champion. Bladefist is mine.
Cutting down unarmed prisoners? Why not fight a real battle?

Text1: Master Velen, I have never led soldiers before. Are you sure--

Text: You are capable of more than you know, Yrel.
Now go. The Rangari follow your orders. Find the prisoners.
Just be ready when our ships arrive at Karabor.

Text1: Nyami! We are here -
What is this? Oh, no... no...
You have to stop them!
...The protector... still answers her call... you'll have to defeat it!
Ahhh!
Are YOU, Tuulani, and your outsider friends.
Try as you might, this place is doomed. It is only a matter of time...
Yes! Yes! The crystal hums... just a bit of focus and...

Text: Look out behind you!
Text1: Look out behind you!

Text: I think I got him.
Text1: I think I got him.

Text: You have my thanks.
Text1: You have my thanks.

Text: Praise the Light!
Text1: Praise the Light!

Text: A weapon!
Text1: A weapon!

Text: Now, let's see how THEY like being cut open!
Text1: Now, let's see how THEY like being cut open!

Text: At last, freedom!
Text1: At last, freedom!

Text: Farewell, my love.
Text1: Farewell, my love.

Text: Thank the Light!
Text1: Thank the Light!

Text: I thought I was going to die here.
Text1: I thought I was going to die here.

Text: You have no idea how long I've been waiting to do this.
Text1: You have no idea how long I've been waiting to do this.

Text: Die, pig!
Text1: Die, pig!

Text: I will avenge you, Tannosh.
Text1: I will avenge you, Tannosh.

Text: Go with the Light, sister.
Text1: Go with the Light, sister.

Text: May your spirit find rest with those of your people's ancestors.
Text1: May your spirit find rest with those of your people's ancestors.

Text: Kill them. Kill them all.
Text1: Kill them. Kill them all.

Text: Make them suffer, like I suffered.
Text1: Make them suffer, like I suffered.

Text: Thanks.
Text1: Thanks.

Text: I've never held a weapon before.
Text1: I've never held a weapon before.

Text: It feels good.
Text1: It feels good.

Text: Ooh!
Text1: Ooh!

Text: You give my people hope, stranger.
Text1: You give my people hope, stranger.

Text: Dagg tanks you, friend! <Dagg lets out a guttural chuckle.>
Dunno how dem orcs keep catchin' me. <Dagg snickers disarmingly.>
Hi again.

Gonna have to ask demself, "Did Dagg get catched or did Dagg catched dem?"

Big hero been blowin' Dagg's cover! But you special, Dagg t'inks. Dagg is master of dis guys and want to join you.

Dagg is unanimous in dis.
Unanimously agree with Dagg? (Garrison Follower)
Text1: Unanimously agree with Dagg? (Garrison Follower)

Text: Don' blow Dagg's cover!$B$BDey never question a tree.$B$BDagg is unanimous in dis.

Don' let dem see us talkin'!

Dey never question a two-head.

Dagg is unanimous in dis.
Shh! Act natural.
Shh! Don' blow my cover.
I am afraid I must depart and rejoin our pack at Wor'gol. Aka'Magosh.
Out of the way, peon!
Text1: Out of the way, peon!

Text: This acolyte and I will retrieve the rest of our group. Do everything in your power to stop that orc from opening that portal!

Text1: We will return with help.

Text: No... NO! This cannot be the fate of my people!
Ner'zhul leads us to this destiny. To save Karabor, we must stop him.
Meet me back at Twilight Glade, champion. We have much to do.
Good people of Fort Wrynn, our commander has finalized construction on a new building!
We're going to need to work together to get it up to full production. See to it our commander is not kept waiting!
Yo everybody, listen up. Thanks to our commander we got a new building up!
We gotta get this new structure up to snuff pronto, alright? Get to it yesterday!
You can handle things from here, I'm sure. Well done!
You won't be needin' me, you're in charge after all.

Text1: I'll take this draenei back to Khadgar. Stop that orc from opening that portal!
We will return with help.

Text: Power fluctuator active. Rebooting core systems. Please wait.
Alright, Pleasure-Bot 8000. Get back to work!
Command unrecognized. Will only accept commands from Pleasure-Bot 8000 owner: $p.
Damn it all, I give up. $p, you can have him! I'm done!
Alright, Pleasure-Bot 8000. Execute command X47G5!
That's it, I've had it! $p, you can have him! I'm going back to tank-building from here on out!
Ah, sweet freedom! You won't regret this, commander. I'll make you the finest armaments in all of Draenor!
Let's see what we have to work with.
The forge is the soul of the foundry. This one's small but with the right equipment I can enhance it.
These look good, with some modifications I should be able to load them into the cannons for a burst shot.
Shhh! Don't let dem see us talkin' or you'll blow my cover!
I'll see if I can get this thing goin'. Khadgar, buy me some time!
We will do what we can, Thaelin.
$n, keep these orcs off of us!

Text1: Tank coming over the rise! Look out!

Text: These controls don't make SENSE. Remind me never ta drive a tank built by an orc.
Hold strong, everyone. Here they come!
They're bringin' up explosives! $n, destroy those carts before they get close!
There's so many of them...
Don't you give up yet, paladin.
That's it! I've got 'er runnin'! Let's finish this.
Ahh ha ha haaa! Nice shot!
Very well, but don't take long. I will require both of you later, and you will need to be alive.
Come, Cordana!
I am forming a small party to scout the enemy's fortifications.
Text1: I am forming a small party to scout the enemy's fortifications.

Text: Thrall, take command of the remaining survivors and meet us up ahead.
Text1: Thrall, take command of the remaining survivors and meet us up ahead.

Text: Maraad, take command of the remaining survivors and meet us up ahead.
Text1: Maraad, take command of the remaining survivors and meet us up ahead.

Text: It will be done.
Yes, Archmage.
Up ahead! Look at that!
Ancestors help us... look at that!
I know what I must do.
BLOOD AND HONOR!
KILROGG DEADEYE
Text1: KILROGG DEADEYE

Text: WARLORD OF THE BLEEDING HOLLOW
Text1: WARLORD OF THE BLEEDING HOLLOW

Text: Look what dragged itself through my jungle. Fresh meat!
We won't go without a fight, Deadeye.
It looks like you could use a hand.
No! Fight me instead!
GOOOO... FIND... KHADGARRRR....

Text1: Yay! Thank you thank you thank you SO much!

Text: I thought everyone forgot about me. Thank you, $Gkind mister:kind lady;!
Wow, did you fight off all the orcs? You're strong!

Text1: <The little girl wails inconsolably.>

Text: With luck, the small ones will now flee, and we can begin construction.
We won't go without a fight, Deadeye.
Mm.
This slaver and torturer knows nothing of honor.
We cannot hide here forever.
Step into my arena and die with honor.
You have entered my arena, strangers. You will either leave it as victors, or as corpses.
Such is the way of the SHATTERED HAND.
A combat arena. This may be a trap, but at least we will die with honor.

Text1: Hurry, Yrel. Your hammer's might will help us greatly.

Text: I'll move forward and scout their gates while you're taking out those catapults. Lok'tar ogar!
Commander, Over here!
Damn these ogres and their magic! I can't find a way to bring the barrier down so we're just going to have to sneak in around it.
I'll go first and clear the way, meet me on the other side.
Blood and thunder, what a battle!
Let's kill some ogres!
Fly with me, hero. We will assist them from above!
The purifying light of the naaru is both our hammer AND shield.
They are at the very temple gates - fly closer! Hurry!
Circle back. We must clear the steps.
Exarch Akama! Watch your flanks!
Thank you, old friend!
Never again will you orcish hordes darken the light of Karabor!
Press onward. By the light of the naaru!
Carry the light, brothers and sisters!
We've done all we can from up here...
We did it! We broke the blockade!
We've broken the main siege. We should meet with our forces on the ground.
These are the last of our forces. We'll stay here to hold the temple gates.
Champion, I need you to fight your way to the harbor.

Text1: I'll approach the enemy from the south. Light of the naaru, guide you.
Champion, the naaru has come to aid us. We must defend it while it gathers power!
We've done it! Now to put an end to this assault...

Text: Witness the TRUE power of the Iron Horde!
ENOUGH. Play time is over. I will deal with you myself.

Text1: Up there! The fleet commander shows himself.
What is the naaru doing?

Text: It is done. Victory is ours!

Text1: Hero, you fought fearlessly. For that, please accept my thanks.

Text: Greetings, savior of my people!
If you are hearing this message, it means that I am no more - but Karabor is safe.
I owe you an explanation.
The naaru that we draenei revere are creatures of pure light.
But if their death is near, they lose their essence, collapsing into creatures of shadow.
When we draenei first arrived on this world, naaru accompanied us. But they could not stop our vessel from crashing.
The "Dark Star" that appeared in the skies above Draenor that terrible night was no celestial body.
It was a fallen naaru, ejected from our vessel in moments of panic and terror. Its name was K'ara.
What was once a creature of faith and beauty became a dark and hungering God, a living font of darkness.
We owed K'ara a great debt. Without the naaru's aid, my people would never have escaped our homeworld of Argus.
To see K'ara's transformation into shadow was a heavy burden to bear. When the naaru returned to us... I did what I had to do.
Remember, life is the light, and light is life itself. They may be exchanged, but nothing is ever lost.
Darkness... comes...
The shadows grow closer!
The Dark Star approaches...
The void will consume all...
Tank ya, mon. Dese Warsong be trixie an' got de drop on ol' J'wan.
I'm off ta Samedi's realm. I be seein' ya.
WARLORD BLACKHAND
Text1: WARLORD BLACKHAND

Text: LEADER OF THE BLACKROCK ORCS
Text1: LEADER OF THE BLACKROCK ORCS

Text: I 'preciate da blessin', mon. De Lord of de Grave smile upon ya.
Dey's someting in Oshu'gun pullin' on me soul. I gonna hava look.
What dis? I be dead!
I gonna haunt dese Warsong foreva. Stay away from de voodoo.
AHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH!
Text1: AHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH!

Text: Furies of the Throne of Elements, we answer your call. How may we serve?
Commander! When I heard the ogre's death cry I came as soon as I could. Did everything go well?
Someone call for a lift?
You three! Follow $p onto the battlefield, and listen for my call.
I have a plan.
And the Raven Mother spoke to me: Krikka, you are my dear child. You shall seek out my other wayward children and bring them back to the nest.
When all of the flock have gathered the end shall come. The world will be torn asunder in a great catastrophe! Fear not, for the Raven Mother will save us!
The Raven Mother will come from the heavens for her children. We will rise upon her great ebon wings to take our rightful place in her dark kingdom!
Until that time comes give your praise to the Raven Mother! Look after her great kin for guidance and strength. May she cast her shadow upon you!
Scribe! Did you get all of that?
Yes, High Ravenspeaker.
Praise the Raven Mother!
With the keystone, you will be able to pass through, alone. Once inside, deactivate their shields and we will join you.

Text1: Ared would not want to see me standing here crying like this. Let's go to this armory of yours.
This looks amazing! If only Ared was alive to see this, he would be so proud!

Text: The docks. Run to the docks. Run. RUN!
Come at me, Hellscream!
Don't be a fool, Ga'nar - Run! We will fight another day.

Text1: Look out!
Keep moving. I see the ships ahead.

Text: Their entire army is behind us.

Text1: Their entire army is behind us.

Text: Where now?
Head for the ships at the end of the road.
This way. Go, go, go!
There is no place to run, outsiders. This is MY world. We will find you!
We Frostwolves will be waiting for you, Hellscream! You, your ogres, your whole Iron Horde... You're as good as dead!
Ignore his threats. We will go to Shadowmoon for reinforcements. This time, the draenei will triumph.
Let's get underway then. We will need to build a stronghold if we hope to end the Iron Horde threat. And we're going to need help from the natives.
To Shadowmoon!
To the home of the Frostwolves!

Text1: I'll move forward and scout their gates while you're taking out those catapults. Dioniss aca.
Commander, over here!
That magical barrier is too strong for our explosives to break open. I can't find a way to bring it down so we're going to have to sneak in around it.
I'll go first and clear the way, meet me on the other side.

Text: That danged army should be here any minute. Let's move!
Personnel evacuation system engaged.

Text1: By the light, what a battle!
Lets do this!

Text: That was close.
There is no turning back. We press on, through the very jaws of the beast.
Who knew the draenei held such... delicious treasures in their temple?
Do you dare challenge me, defenders of Auchindoun?!
Sever my bonds... and the portal falls...
Such decadence... it will all burn.
Yes... Yes!
Grommash will pay for his arrogance.
The legion comes for you.... We will feast on these souls.
Do not delay, mortal. I can feel the life-essence of your armies fading. There will be time for regret later...
We will meet again... $n.
Gul'dan, such foolishness. This gift... so much more than you could ever know....
Long have I waited...
...hungered... to be more...
And now, all shall bow before me!
The bonds weaken. Freedom will be mine!
Everyone - find cover!

Text1: Giving away our position. The fool brought a genesaur down on us.

Text: What do we have here? A hero? Gorgrond is no place for heroes, my friend.
They fired on Veil Akraz!
It's just... gone...
Come, we must go!
Free at last.
I swear, by the spirit of my father, I WILL MAKE THEM PAY.
Gah!
Ugh - oh!
Well now.
I'd say we made an impact.
Looks like we arrived just in time.
Free at last! Join me in the ogre mound when you are done, and we shall slay the ogre chieftain together.
Bring them to me alive, Roltall. They will fetch an excellent price.
The Iron Horde have landed upon these shores. It is our task to make them regret it.
In here!
We cannot stay here long. Soon, the entirety of the Iron Horde will be upon us.
$n, our champion, will stay back and disrupt the enemy camp. The rest of us will seek safe passage through the jungle.
Good luck, $n.
Fight well, $n.
AAAAAAHHHHHHHHHH!

Text1: Exarch, have your soulbinders meet me at my camp. I intend to stop Teron'gor before he unleashes more demons.

Text: We must stop Teron'gor before this world falls... as so many others have.
Don't worry, $n. We've got your back!

Text1: Come on, we need to get going pronto!

Text: Here you are, miss Pinchwhistle!

Text1: About time! Come on, Gazwitz.
Of course, ma'am.
Supervising of course. Now, get moving!

Text: Well done, $n.
This cave will serve us well.
Follow me, and stay close.
Now - kill your hundred, or die trying!
Sorry, but we don't have that kind of time.
Hmph. I only counted ninety-nine kills, wizard.
Then I guess we owe you one.
Everyone, with me!
Quickly! Into the cave, before they thaw.
We've done all we can from up here...
After them! Don't let them get away!
I am pleased. I could watch you rats fight for hours.
Exarch Maladaar, take Qiana with you and scout the cave.
As you wish.
$n - I have a special job for you.
Lady Liadrin, take Olin with you and scout the cave.

Text1: At your command.

Text: Your scurrying is at an end, rats.
Not so fast, Ner'zhul.
Yes... step closer! I will bury you alive for the glory of the Iron Horde!
Worthless...
I've seen it in my dreams... these strangers from other worlds would burn everything we've fought for.
But it is orc blood that runs in the veins of Draenor!
Go forth, Iron Horde!  Make corpses of our enemies.
For the glory of Grommash!
Where is my power, ogre?
Your power? (It's MY power!)
You will obey, disciple. Hand over its reins.
I think not. (We're done taking orders from you!)
We've learned much from K'ure. (We're writing a book.)
You're insane.
Run away, old man. (Soon Highmaul will burn. Then, the world!)
In death... I am free...
Those Iron cowards were using us as conduits to power their portal. They will regret that.
The Shadow Council thanks you.
Seek out Gul'dan if you truly wish to stop the Iron Horde. (Gul'dan! Gul'dan powers the portal!)
Gul'dan! Gul'dan powers the portal!
I admit, even in Socrethar's madness, there was a hint of truth.
He questioned our complacency. Perhaps we have been too content, too SAFE, hiding here on Draenor.
A call is coming, hero. I feel it, large and looming, just beyond the horizon. When the time  comes, the draenei must answer.

Text1: Today, we have defeated one of Gul'dan's strongest allies.
Without their leader, the Sargerei will crumble. The Auchenai will soon be able to reclaim their city.
For now, we can consider this a monumental victory. Thank you, hero.

Text: Our only course of action is to retreat. Everyone, with me!
Cho'gall!
Guards! Stop him!
Seal the gates! Protect the palace! Highmaul will never fall to the likes you.
You thought to imprison us, Mar'gok? (You could never control us!)
Destroy them all. Raze this city to the ground! (The stones will be ours! All shall fall to darkness!)
Operations in Tanaan go well. The Citadel is almost complete.
I am keeping a close eye on the Highmaul ogres, Warchief. So far, they remain... obedient.
What of you, Blackhand?
Alliance and Horde forces strike at the Foundry, but they are nothing I cannot handle.
Again, Blackhand? All I hear are excuses.
Azuka! How goes the search for the alpha?

Text1: Well, Warchief. We need only the Heart of Gorgorek to give it life.

Text: Good. I will have you deal with the other-worlders as well. Or... do you lack the bloodlust of your forefathers?

Text1: My blade skills surpass those of my sires, Warchief. I can clean up Blackhand's mess.

Text: Hrahh... I will slice off your tongue for that!
Ahahaha... bold words from my newest Warlord. Very well!
Carry forth your ancestral blade. Bathe it in the blood of our enemies. Show me its legendary power.
Prove yourself, Azuka, and I shall esteem you among my Warlords.

Text1: Don't worry, little mouse. I haven't forgotten about you. I'll take care of you... later.

Text: Hang tight, $Gsir:my lady;. I'm here to help you.
Don't worry about me. I know my way around here.
I'll poke around here. See if you can find anything elsewhere in the camp.
What do you know about Grommash Hellscream's plans?
Text1: What do you know about Grommash Hellscream's plans?

Text: Grommash Hellscream met with his Warlords - Blackhand, Kargath Bladefist, Kilrogg Deadeye, and Azuka Bladefury. I'd watch out for Azuka... it seems she is charged with destroying the Alliance forces here on Draenor.

<Written on a nearby piece of paper:$B$BWe have uncovered Gorgorek the Worldrender, an ancient magnaron frozen in the stone pools of Gorgrond.$B$BThe Warsong elders believe this magnaron was a once-powerful alpha, with the ability to command lesser beings of its own kind.$B$BAncient clan records suggest that the beast can be awakened.>
Text1: <Written on a nearby piece of paper:$B$BWe have uncovered Gorgorek the Worldrender, an ancient magnaron frozen in the stone pools of Gorgrond.$B$BThe Warsong elders believe this magnaron was a once-powerful alpha, with the ability to command lesser beings of its own kind.$B$BAncient clan records suggest that the beast can be awakened.>

Text: <Scraps of paper surround the map of Blackrock Foundry. They look like manufacturing orders for war machines.>
Text1: <Scraps of paper surround the map of Blackrock Foundry. They look like manufacturing orders for war machines.>

Text: <This map bears many markings within Tanaan Jungle, including drawings of fortifications and troop movements. Hellscream seems quite interested in that region.>
Text1: <This map bears many markings within Tanaan Jungle, including drawings of fortifications and troop movements. Hellscream seems quite interested in that region.>
Kajassa got ya, mon. I be here ta help ya.
Shhhh... keep dem eyes an' ears open.

Text: I've heard of Warlord Bladefury. She is a masta a da blade, undefeated across da orc clans. Those who underestimate her, die.
She be ambitious, clever, an' cruel. Now dat she has risen ta Warlord, we had betta watch our backs.
I have heard of Warlord Bladefury. She is a master of the blade. Many underestimate her, but she is undefeated across the orc clans.
She is ambitious, clever, and cruel. Now that she has risen to power, I fear we must face her soon.
Is everyone in their places? Good, let us begin!
It was written in the "Tome of the Falling Sands", "Time waits for no one". The Raven Mother knew we would have one who is not of the flock here for the ritual! Oh, You are truly blessed!
Get on in there, champ!
[Placeholder Scene!]
What good are a handful of slaves against the Blackrock war machine?
Blackrocks... CRUSH THEM!
Khadgar! Get us out of here!

Text1: So it is true. The heart CAN infuse life into these creatures.
Ah, hero... I knew you would come. You are just in time to witness the heart's power.
This magnaron walked Draenor before the first orc took breath. And now, it... and an endless army of these destroyers... bend to MY will!
Follow me, $n. She's up this way.

Text: But first... I think I need to wash my hands. I will meet you back at your camp.
Commander, what's wrong?

Text1: Argghh! Looks like we'll have to deal with that gronn.
Well, at least we took care of that thing. Come on, hero. We'd better report this back to headquarters.

Text: What progress do you have to report? This better not be like last time!

Text1: We have learned how to dominate the minds of gronn.

Text: Good. Finish your work and bring them to me.

Text1: Yes, Commander Gar.

Text: Many leagues of deadly land yet stand between us and the Blackrock.

Text1: We should have brought an army to fight the Iron Horde!
Ha! Your size makes you weak, giant.

Text: They took Corporal Thukmar!

Text1: For the light!

Text: Commander, our aerial squadron has weakened the magnaron, but we're pinned out here. We need your help to assault the main compound.
I don't like da look a' dis ting, hero.

Text1: Ah, welcome, Vindicator Yrel. I see you have come for Maladaar's trial.
The spirits sense your purpose. They already grow eager to challenge you.
It is my honor to face the heroes of the ancient past. They will not find me lacking.
Good luck, Lady Yrel.

Text: Yrel, this is how I always wished to see you. Do not let me down.

Text1: Greetings, teacher. Let me show you what I have learned in my travels.

Text: You have exceeded all my hopes, Yrel. You may proceed.

Text1: Now, to lay Maraad's ashes to rest.

Text: Yrel... how you have grown since last we met. But... is it enough? Are you worthy of leading our people?
Now, it is my turn to test your strength.
When you face a more powerful foe, will you stand strong?

Text1: Do not fear, for I will stand!

Text: When our people look to you, will you be ready to command?

Text1: I shall not let them down!

Text: When all hope is lost, will you... still... fight?

Text1: I shall never yield!
I... can...

Text: When you look inside yourself and see only darkness, can you still find the Light?
What was that?

Text1: Because... in this world... we are never...
Hero! Use the hammer, now!

Text: Yrel... it is true. The student has surpassed the teacher. You are ready.
If only Prophet Velen could see you now... he would be proud.
Rise, Yrel. It is your charge to unite the draenei. Prepare them for what's to come.
Farewell...

Text1: Maraad, my friend... be at peace.
Thank you, hero. I will meet up with you later. I just need a moment to pay my respects to the ancestors.

Text: One final trial awaits, Yrel. US!
You have chosen your champion. Now, let us begin!
Ahh, I am defeated.

Text1: Such strength!

Text: I submit!
Yrel, today, you have completed the trials of the exarch.
You have proven courage, kindness, faith, and strength... pillars upon which our society has arisen.
However, we measure a leader not only by her merit, but also by the character of her companions.
Champion, we have watched you throughout this trial.
We saw your bravery in Frostfire, your persistence in Nagrand, and your loyalty in Auchindoun.
Your dedication to Lady Yrel proves to us that she is worthy. We did not choose the next Exarch. YOU did.
Yrel, do not forget that an exceptional leader inspires greatness in others. Trust in your people, and trust in yourself.
Now, RISE...
EXARCH YREL!

Text1: Gaze upon the source of your demise, heroes.
This magnaron walked Draenor before the first orc took breath.  And now it bends to my will.
It will crush your armies and your pitiful fortress.  But first, it will crush YOU!

Text: The beast is defeated, but we cannot rest yet. One enemy still remains.
I am needed near the gates. Warchief Hellscream has been spotted on the battlefield.
Find Bladefury. Bring me her head!
Taz'dingo! Well fought, mon. But we ain't leavin' until da she-orc be dead.
I be needed near da main gate. Dey say Grommash has joined da battle.
Take care a  Bladefury. Bring me her head!

Text1: I grow tired of our games, little mouse. It's time to finish this.
My blade thirsts for your blood!
No... noooo... Warchief... I have... failed you...
Halt! Hellscream approaches.

Text: Look! Hellscream shows himself.

Text1: The battle is finished! We've routed the Iron Horde and pushed them back to the gates!

Text: The Iron Horde is never beaten! I will NEVER surrender!
I will remember this day, heroes. I will remember your names and your faces, and when the time comes, I will carve you limb from limb.
The entrance to the main vestibule opens!
The barrier behind Exarch Hataaru slides open!
The teleporter to the central platform is now active!

Text1: ALONE!

Text: Thanks, pal! You're a life saver!
Knowledge is half the battle.
Keep your wits about you, commander.
The battle is heating up. We must push forward!
This is our chance to send the Iron Horde scattering. Steel yourself. We must hold the front line!
Good luck $r, I am going to find a nice warm fire!

Text1: Good luck, $r. Don't waste time, ever!

Text: If you dare challenge me, I will be waiting in Tanaan Jungle. You will find only death beyond these gates.

Text1: Follow me, hero!
Give up, Grommash! Look around you. You are beaten!
Very well, Grommash... then we will come for you.
Congratulations, hero. This victory is ours.

Text: Commander, our rylak riders have weakened da magnaron, but we're pinned outside. We need ya help ta break inta da main compound.

Text1: The battle is finished. We've pushed the Iron Horde army back to the gates.

Text: Lay down your weapons, Grommash! Look around you. You are lost.
Wait then, Grommash. Wait, because we are coming for you.
Thank you, hero.  Today, we taste victory! Lok'tar ogar!
My next pet won't be so easy!
All's fair in tiny monkeys and war.
What? How?? I will have my revenge, you liver-scented codswallup!
A fitting conclusion to yet another epic battle, featuring me!
Prepare for the smiting of a lifetime!
Ah, lucky for you I was not paying attention this time!
As powerful as I am, I cannot be everywhere at once.
But you, commander, are my greatest resource. Between the skill of your allies and the might of your garrison, there is not a stronghold that can withstand you.
Under your leadership, the full might of the Alliance expeditionary force will engage the Iron Horde.
Under your command, the Horde's greatest warriors will engage Grommash and his army.
But I will be concentrating on the single greatest threat to the safety of Azeroth:
Gul'dan. Darkness incarnate.
In all my years, Gul'dan is the craftiest, most diabolical foe I have ever encountered. I hold myself accountable for his release.
We MUST find and eliminate Gul'dan and his nascent Shadow Council network.
With your help, I can track him down. I will ask a great deal of you. I will task you to the very edge of your abilities.
But I will also help you as much as I am able. Together we will create for you an artifact of legendary power.
With a core forged from the heart of Draenor's sun, this ring is a foundation upon which we will build a wonder.
...there! It is done. Now to find Gul'dan.
Follow me, commander!
Once we locate Gul'dan, we may have to move quickly...
My eyes are open: Van shalach, om aeschis, khaz'tolim!
Come on, come on... Where are you...
Wait - here - what...?
Hiding! He's countering my spell.
Champion, killing Teron'gor must've shaken him up. That's good. But now he knows we're getting closer.
We need... more power!

Text1: We'll track you from the air!

Text: The trail will not be easy to follow. Start by heading east.

Text1: Follow the trail of time anomalies like this.
Here! It looks like Garrosh came down this way alone after he first arrived on Draenor. But where was Kairoz?

Text: Look at Garrosh. His hands are bound. But he's alone. When did he and Kairoz part ways?

Text1: Hmmm... That ogre shouldn't be here. Something strange must've happened up on this ridge.

Text: Who is that?

Text1: That's Kairoz in disguise. Garrosh killed him! But where was the body?

Text: We must be close!
I know now how to defeat Gul'dan's magic and reveal the Shadow Council. But we'll need more power.
We will have to tear artifacts from the very heart of the Ogre Empire.
I can help you. Let us augment the power of that ring of yours...
Hold out your hand, and step into the light!
I'm sorry, I should've mentioned that you would be... slightly killed.
Marvelous... we have everything we need!
Gul'dan will NOT be able to hide from my gaze this time.

Text1: Archmage, be careful.

Text: We have him where we want him!
My eyes are open: Val'mir, khar abra, mal ozymius...
Come, come, come... I will find you...
...there! Gul'dan! He is -
You! The human mage from Tanaan...
I have found you!
I've been inquiring about you, "Khadgar." It would seem we have a history.
Then you know how this ends. Give yourself up.
Your clumsy magic works both ways. I have also found you.

Text1: Archmage, look ou-

Text: Foolish mage. Your death will be excruciatingly slow. I only wish I could be there to enjoy it.

Text1: Champion - The archmage!
Be still, Khadgar. Garona's dagger was enchanted.

Text: %s groans in pain.

Text1: This wound is grisly. You should see a priest.

Text: No - no priest. Cordana, stitch me up.
Come, this way. This will only hurt - well, quite a bit actually.
The power once reserved for the Sorcerer Kings, I place in your hands.
Omnivus, al-vitrade! Arcanum totalus!

Text1: These are dangerous forces you're working with, archmage.

Text: Our friend needs them. The hardest trials are yet to come.

Text1: I'll be keeping my eyes on you.
Good luck, champion. Be careful in that foundry!

Text: Now, stand perfectly still.
This magic is extremely reliable and - maybe a tiny bit fatal. Hold still, I said!
I draw my strength, from the HEART of Draenor...
Come, Grommash. Drink.
I told you - get out!
They assault your foundry. They murder your allies. Mine is the only way.
Go!

Text1: It worked.

Text: I maintain a pair of goblin jumper cables for just such an emergency. Are you well, commander?
Come with me. Gul'dan will not give up control of his pet without a fight.

Text1: Just kill me and be done with it, archmage.

Text: I'm not here to kill you, assassin.

Text1: %s reels in pain.

Text: Where is your master? Tell me!

Text1: Burn... in a thousand... hells...

Text: You first. Where is Gul'dan!?

Text1: Argghgh - he - will undo you -

Text: Where is he hiding?

Text1: Archmage...

Text: TELL ME!

Text1: %s grasps her head.
Khadgar, stop! What's the difference between this and torture?

Text: But she knows...

Text1: I don't even know what you're fighting for anymore.

Text: You - you're right. Gul'dan has butchered her mind already.
I am sorry, Garona. We will find another way.
If she is searching for this "Heart of Gorgorek," then we must find it before her. I will notify you as soon as I learn more.
Commander, this will be a protracted campaign. I should have more information for you in a week's time.
If she and da Iron Horde be searchin' for dis "Heart a Gorgorek," den we must find it first. I will send for ya when I hear more.
Commander, dis will be a long campaign. I will have more information for ya in a week's time.
It looks like everyone is in position. Ka'alu, give the signal and get us out of here!
There are still Iron Horde in the northern courtyard.
Gro the Uncreator, I call to you!
The spirits of the Laughing Skull have spoken. We must join together to fight our common enemy, the Iron Horde!
Yes! It is working! The spirits were right!
Xuk...
Ahhh, there it is. There's MY artifact. How foolish of me to trust Brak with something so valuable.
It's a shame that you're too late to stop me. Surrender the artifact, and I will allow you to escape with your lives.
Hahahaha, so be it! IRON HORDE, ADVANCE!
See what weapons I have in my arsenal!
You will never withstand the might of Goc!
RELEASE THE IRON STARS!
Gronnlings, attack!
ARGH... UNBELIEVEABLE! You will DIE for your insolence! I'LL TEAR YOU LIMB FROM LIMB!
NO! I will DIE before I let you take what is mine! YOU... WILL NOT... WIN... THIS... WAR! AAARRRRGHH!
Hahaha! Not so confident now, are we?! Face me on even ground, cowards!
The Laughing Skull will rise again!

Text1: It is done! As for you, I think it is fitting that one of my tools dispatches the others...

Text: For Skettis!
You trust your eyes too much, fool.

Text1: The Light prevails, because WE stand against the darkness.
What ARE these creatures?

Text: Go ahead, Ga'nar. Take the clan. Slay your own brother in cold blood. See who follows you then.
You think THIS is what father wanted?
My totem will empower you!
Stand nearby to use my totem's strength.
Stand beside my totem to gain its power.

Text1: My wolves will tear your pets apart!
%s glares intensely at you.

Text: Come! You have your orders. I ride for Tanaan.
I only hope my people will understand.

Text1: Oh, this should be interesting.  You don't mind if I take notes, do you?
It's easy to see why objects such as these would have been highly prized by their cultures!  Er, sorry about your pets.
Very interesting results.  Thanks for helping me test them out!
Well, what can you expect from something that's been buried in the ground for a millennium?
In its native culture, that pet might have been revered as a martyr.
Huh, I kinda thought that might happen.
Fortunately, Gyraxle can repair anything.  Even himself.
Now, was that result the device performing as expected, or did it just explode?
All in the name of science.
I've got bandages in my field kit if you need some...
You have to respect the ingenuity of such an ancient device.
I'll add a special thanks to your pet when I publish this research.
Here we go!
Oh my pets did so good.  They're going to get so many extra snuggles for that.
Oh, that's okay I guess.  Doodle will need a new eye though.
Don't worry, I'll kiss the boo-boo all better.
Soup will make you all better!
Oh no!
She's not dead, she's just sleeping.
We'll put the rainbow bandage on that.
Oh no!
Is your pet sleeping too?
You can make your pet all better, right?
You are lucky my wolves are not yet full grown, or else you would have been the meal.
Only defeat truly exposes our weaknesses.  This loss will improve their training.
That one was too stupid.
That one did not lack courage.
That one won't make that mistake again.
That one was too slow.
That one will need some healing.
A good kill.
A clean kill.
Hardly even a challenge.
Why are your pets so weak?
An easy kill.  My wolves will learn nothing.

Text: Gladiators, kill!
I remain the greatest warlord in all of Nagrand!
What?  How is this possible?  You must have cheated!
What is one death when I have an army of three?
My gladiators fight to the death!
You make Tarr angry!
I told you to kill, not die!
Haha, puny $r has puny pets.
Gladiator smash!
Are you not entertained?
Tarr will rock you!
This is why Tarr is the greatest warlord in all of Nagrand!

Text1: I may be small, but if you hurt my pets, I'll hurt you.
Thanks $gMister:Lady;!  I bet 100 coppers on this fight.
This is just like the time my home town was overrun by demons.
It's okay, they're used to dying.
Not the first time someone has hunted that one to the ends of the earth.
Easy now!  I paid a pretty copper for that one.
I'll sell ya a Stone of Jordan if you promise not to do that again.
Bad luck just runs in my family.
Sorry, $gMister:Lady;.
Don't throw that one away, it can still be fixed up.
That's right!  My pets are from the mean streets of Caldeum.
That's a bit of bad luck there, $gMister:Lady;.

Text: Our hopes lie in what these pets will become.  They are sacred to us.
Glory to Anzu!
We are Arakkoa.  We are not broken by a single defeat.
A bad omen.
Anzu protect your children!
No!  The guardians cannot fall!
Doom and gloom!  Dooooooooom and glooooooom!
The curse of Sethe is upon us.
A good omen.
The strength of the Arakkoa is with us.
The raven god blesses us today.
The guardians stand strong.
Anzu protects his children.

Text1: Pay attention, $n.  Strength is often found where you least expect it.
I hope you have learned something today.
I hope you have learned something today.
I am sad for the loss, but glad for your victory.
Fear not, a simple healing spell will set that to rights.
Life is full of surprises.
The Light has not yet taken her.  She simply rests.
The moth is drawn to the flame, it seems.
Life is full of surprises.
It is folly to underestimate the stength of nature.
The moth is delicate, but not without defenses.
Do not despair. Both you and your pet can learn from this.
A tender lesson learned too late.

Text: The darkness... it flows within me. It seeps from every vein.
Come, strangers! Cross into the realm of the Shadow Lands! I shall deliver you to your death.
Any bites yet?  I have found that patience (and beer) really helps bring in the big catch!
Did you bring a cooler?  Don't EVER go fishing without a cooler!
Any bites yet?  I have found that patience (and beer) really helps bring in the big catch!
*HIC!*  Was that a dolphin?!  *HIC!*  I love dolphins!
Seriously?  I think I would actually just throw that one back.
See ya!
I will be back later, save me a beer!
Good luck on the lunkers!
Howdy $n!  Any luck out here?
$n, I found ya!
Greetings $n!
The Exarchs are charged with leading the draenei people. We represent and uphold the values of our society.

Text1: It's been years since I've been out in the field like this.$B$B<The stately archmage takes a deep breath.>$B$BThere's nothing like the smell of clean air and danger.
If it were up to me, I'd be the one to carry out this mission. But Archmage Khadgar insisted that you would have a more delicate touch.

I still bear old wounds from the demons' first coming to Azeroth. I remember the horror, the madness, and the stillness that descended upon a city destroyed.$B$BI will do anything in my power to prevent that from happening again.
I cannot fathom why anyone would pledge themselves to the Legion.$B$BThere are those who lust for power, and do not know how to wield it.

The Sargerei village is like a beehive.$B$BDisturb its denizens, and we will get stung. Destroy it in flames, and we will destroy the precious honeycomb as well.$B$BThe only way to retrieve the information we seek is through sublety.
Exarch Othaar's betrayal was sudden. How could a leader of the draenei turn his back on the Light, and embrace the enemies who persecuted his entire race?
His new allies have given him a new name, and a new identity - "Socrethar." He is a powerful enemy, and I fear what he is capable of.

Have you heard of me, $n? I am Modera, archmage of the Council of Six, which rules the Kirin Tor and Dalaran.$B$BI could wipe out this entire village if I chose.$B$BBut that is not why we are here. As I have learned through the years, sometimes you need honey to catch a fly.
Ah, hero... I knew you would come. Gaze upon the source of your demise!
Now, I will leave you a taste of the Iron Horde's new power!

Text: How about we see who is on the other side of these anomalous shenanigans?
Temporal juxtaposition incoming!
Wow! It worked. And we haven't been temporally inverted.
I'm sorry, Cenarius. I believed in your cause, but I couldn't bring myself to turn against...

Text1: You've done me a great service today, Farondis.
What a shame that you won't LIVE to reap the benefits of my gratitude.

Text: ...what?!

Text1: This whole valley is filled with plotters and schemers.
Cavorting with Cenarius behind my back? I will NOT tolerate dissent!
Here it is, my Prince: The Tidestone of Golganneth, one of the seven Stones of Creation, and treasured relic of the kaldorei.

Text: Very good. Leave me.
Commander, Morthis Whisperwing from the Druids of the Talon was looking for you. He can be found beneath the great tree to the south.
