Text: Rally to me, pack. It's time to end this!
Charge, brothers and sisters! Stop for nothing!
We're gonna load this thing up, row ourselves into that river, and blow us up some trolls. Who's ready for a good time, eh?
I'm gonna pilot this thing. You just tell me where to shoot, and I'll shoot. Let's show these things a good time!
Rokhan's been around for a long time, Princess. He ain't gonna die to some blood trolls!
Yeah that's right buddy, take a walk!
We're gonna blow up your Old God, goblin style!

Text1: Tonight you're sleepin' with the swamp fishies!

Text: Terrible swamp you all got here. Would be real nice if somethin' happened to it!

Text1: <Sigh> Did I really think working with goblins would turn out any other way?
Well excuuuuuuse me, princess!
And BOOM goes the bad guy!

Text: Bet we could blow up a whole lotta gnomes with this baby!
Where's your Blood God now, huh? Bleh, ya creeps!

Text1: Aw! They blow up so fast, I can't even enjoy it! Well... maybe I can enjoy it a little.

Text: Wakey wakey, time to DIE!
That's how goblins from Kezan roll!
Whoa whoa WHOA! Nobody said we'd have to deal with undead!
We WORK with undead all the time, you idiot!

Text1: Uh, boss, I believe the technical term is "Forsaken".

Text: Eh, Princess, I ain't no expert, but I think you guys got a blood troll problem.

Text1: How many more of these goons we gotta blow up before they get the message?

Text: Criminy. I never blew up an Old God before. Maybe I shoulda brought more explosives!
MORE?! Bring it on!
Got it, Princess. You're about to get a front row seat to the latest and greatest of goblin technology!

Text1: Uh, boss... we got some screws missin' in places that the manual clearly says require screws.

Text: Oh, well, yeah... user manuals are for schmucks. Newt, we're doing this live!
This thing ain't a problem, we just gotta use the ol' curveball!
Curveball! Curveball!
YEAH! CURVEBALL!

Text1: We got a BIG problem here!

Text: Haha! Ya tink I gonna let ya die when ya still owe me?
Da rest of dese fellas be all yours. Have fun, but don't forget ya still be payin' me a debt. Send me their souls!
That ain't gonna hit the monster, aim harder!
The city has fallen. Nothing was left in the wake of the battle between Sethraliss and Mythrax. Our loa gave her life to keep us safe, and we will not let that sacrifice be in vain.
Together with Vorrik and Korthek, we sealed the tomb, with the hopes that no one would ever wake the giant buried within. We will not be doomed to repeat the mistakes our neighbors made so long ago.

There is talk within the temple. Korthek is eager to attack the trolls. They are a formidable race that will not fall easily. We've lived in peace for so long... why would he now desire to start a fight he cannot win?
I shall inform Vorrik of my concerns, but first I must safeguard my key. I have a feeling something bad will happen very soon...
Vorrik, if you are receiving this message, then I fear I was too late. Korthek has betrayed our people, and plans to break the barrier we placed on the tomb long ago.

PLACEHOLDER SCENE - Reveal of the true power of the blood trolls, a giant corrupted titan monster, huge armies of blood trolls, and Ateena mocking Talanji. Ends with a horde of blood trolls descended upon everyone.
Text1: PLACEHOLDER SCENE - Reveal of the true power of the blood trolls, a giant corrupted titan monster, huge armies of blood trolls, and Ateena mocking Talanji. Ends with a horde of blood trolls descended upon everyone.

Text: Enough!
It is over, Sylvanas! The walls of Lordaeron will soon come crashing down around you.

Text1: You have no idea what you're up against, boy king. We've only just begun!

Text: I've never seen anything like it...
Anything made can be broken! Genn, follow me!

Text1: DESTROY THEM!

Text: RETREAT!

Text1: No! They must not escape!

Text: This key belongs to the first Keeper. His name was Sulthis, and he died at the hands of Korthek.
Long ago, Mythrax the Unraveler descended upon our lands. He slaughtered all in his path, troll and sethrak alike.
Our loa sacrificed herself to save us from that monstrosity. She struck the C'Thrax down, but not before it was able to destroy the disc at the heart of Atul'Aman.
After witnessing his destruction firsthand, we knew that something must be done to prevent anyone from raising Mythrax again.
Although immensely powerful, Sulthis could not create the barrier alone. Korthek and I lent him our aid, and together, we sealed Mythrax within the great pyramid.
As the sands continued to spread, Korthek grew hungry for war. He plotted to unearth the C'Thrax and use him as a weapon to conquer the continent.
Korthek raised an army of like-minded sethrak, and they began to slaughter those who opposed them... Sulthis was the first to fall, but not before safeguarding his key.
Those of us still loyal to Sethraliss were forced out of our home and into hiding. We have been fighting the Faithless ever since.

Text1: A weapon... dis must be what Jakra'zet is after! A C'Thrax...
We need to warn de princess.

Text: A ship enters the dungeon. Pike expresses grave concern as to why a ship bearing villagers would enter his order's sanctum.
Text1: A ship enters the dungeon. Pike expresses grave concern as to why a ship bearing villagers would enter his order's sanctum.

Text:
PLACEHOLDER SCENE - Talanji asks if things are really over, Rokhan says evil has a way of surviving and he doubts this will be the last we see of this place.
Shot: Close ups of Talanji and Rokhan, then ominous shot of the now revealed pit.
Text1:
PLACEHOLDER SCENE - Talanji asks if things are really over, Rokhan says evil has a way of surviving and he doubts this will be the last we see of this place.
Shot: Close ups of Talanji and Rokhan, then ominous shot of the now revealed pit.
Dis intrusion ends here! None of ya gonna interrupt de mistress!
Please, Rakera. Don't do dis! You'll get yourself killed!

Text: Wh-what?!
Heretic!

Text1: Your visions had best be right about dis.

Text: Ah, he arrives. De loa of...  Hmm...
Mind your tongue, traitor.
Rezan, Rezan...
I am not your subject,
De time of de loa... is done.
De hour of blood approaches.
No! Habutu!
You should have listened to Talanji.
You have grown stagnant, old friend. You let our kingdom rot and decay. But I have foreseen de troll empire rising again.

I give you dis prophecy. De troll empire will rule dis world, last as it was first. And upon its throne shall sit de king, last as he was first, though neither you or I will live as we do to see it. Such is de vision shown to me by MY god...
No more treaties with outsiders... No more bargains with loa. Blood is our path now... De path of G'HUUN!

Text1: Should we go after dem?

Text: No. In time, dey will come to us.
Come, Mythrax. Come, Unraveller. De final seal must be broken.
Now. Shatter the final seal.
Do not be so hasty, now.
I know you see de flames devouring de city.
You can try to subdue us, and likely succeed.

Text1: No... it can't be.

Text: Seems a mage of your... skill... could be very useful right now, hm?
It's killing her own troops...

Text1: Baine, pull them back!

Text: You face the might of Korthek, the Eternal Emperor!
[PH] No more talking, old friend. Surrender your key to Mythrax's prison. You would doom us all!
[PH] You are right about one thing, though. The time for talking is over!
[PH] The key is deep within my fortress, Vorrik. Or did you think that I was foolish enough to carry it on my person?
[PH] Impressive, "old friend." But it will not be enough to stop me!
Nor you. Your father is displeased dat you have brought dese creatures here. He has ordered me to collect you.
Soldiers of the Horde! Your brothers and sisters lie wounded on the battlefield! There is no honor in this victory if we abandon our own!

Text1: Slay them all, champions! Mark my words, King Anduin and his army did not come here for their amusement. They mean to destroy us! Show them no mercy, for they would show you none in return!

Text: We need ta speed things up. Da King has nosey visitors... dat could pose a problem.
You do your part, General, and I will do mine.
Trespassers!
You will die in these dunes...
Quickly, scavenge what you can. Leave the bodies for the vultures.

Text1: Kiro, they're alive! We can't just leave them here...

Text: Azeroth calls tae ye, champion. She offers a gift... one born of her own essence.
I may be her Speaker, but you are her champion. And she needs ye tae fight fer her.
The very Heart of Azeroth!
Soldiers of the Horde, ready your blades! Today, we march on the kaldorei!
Dis is de resting place of de first king of Zandalar. Dazar was stubborn... but now he serves!

Text1: Despite our efforts to maintain order, Kul Tiras has seen an increase in crime, corruption, and piracy. People are losing faith in the Proudmoore Admiralty.
Lord Admiral Katherine Proudmoore now rules in his place, commanding both the military and the guard.
Kul Tiras is made up of several major houses. They were unified under Daelin Proudmoore's leadership, but that gradually changed after his defeat at Theramore.

Text: Stand down! Don't you know who that is?
But sir... Lady Ashvane ordered--
Lady Ashvane? Do you serve Lady Ashvane? Is that Lady Ashvane's crest upon your shield?
No! You serve Kul Tiras! You wear the crest of Proudmoore! And you take your orders from ME.
Now stand down and let them pass. We shall parley in my office.
N-no, sir.
Aye, sir!

Text1: Patch, now!
Beyond Tiragarde Sound are lands held by the Waycrest and Stormsong families.
To the west lies Drustvar, a mountainous region providing most of the kingdom's ore... and some of our toughest warriors.
In Stormsong Valley, to the north, the tidesages of House Stormsong craft and bless the ships of our legendary fleet.
House Waycrest has been a loyal supporter of Proudmoore's rule for centuries, but their recent absence from council meetings has given rise to troubling rumors.
But nobody has heard from the fleet in months! The tidesages have withdrawn into their cloisters and seem uninterested in finding our missing ships.

Text: Nope, never mind. It's ale. We're good.

Text1: We must unite the houses beneath the Proudmoore banner and locate the missing fleet. Otherwise, Kul Tiras could fall apart before this war even begins.

Text: Our warchief has requested you for a mission of great importance... and secrecy.
Not even I know its nature yet.
Has the warchief summoned you?
This doesn't concern you.
How can we aid the warchief if she keeps things from her advisors?
Perhaps my queen would be more open if she were more assured of their loyalty.
Her advisors are loyal...
...to the Horde.

Text1: Ah, there you are. I was beginning to wonder.
I require the services of one whom I can trust completely.
Certain members of the Horde seem to feel my recent actions have been... indiscriminate.
But I understand discretion very well.
To win this war, the Horde needs allies.
The boy king has something that does not belong to him. I want it back.
You are to infiltrate Stormwind and liberate a political prisoner. One who could change the course of the war... in our favor.
Are you up to the task?

Text: We will not fail you... my queen.

Text1: Oh, I know you won't.
No, you idiot, THE OTHER AWAY!
Steady as she goes, helmsman.

Text: Data recovered. Corruption originates from Old God contained within Nazmir.

Text1: An Old God?! Dis is why de blood trolls assault my city...

Text: Three devices were created to seal the corruption.

Text1: Dat's right, Princess!
No. You will cause no more harm to my people. Your madness ends now!
De shield! It has begun to fade!

Text: You heard the princess! Let 'er rip!
Halt! State your intentions!
Clear the way! Dangerous prisoners coming through!

Text1: I see the city guard is as disciplined as ever. My father was so proud of them.
And now they see me as a criminal.

Text: Get those civilians back! Form a perimeter!

Text1: Mommy, who is that lady?
Come on, we're going home. Now!
Lady Jaina... Is that really her?

Text: It's the daughter of the sea!
Traitor!
Text1: Traitor!

Text: Murderer!
Text1: Murderer!

Text: Sh-she's come back to finish us!

Text1: I will suffer what I must...
I suppose I have earned this.
Do not concern yourself with a few petty crimes. We have far more important matters to address.

Text: Traitor! Seize her!
My king, de Horde has only come to steal our navy for their undead warchief.

Text1: Dis champion defied de might of Stormwind to save Zul and me. Such bravery merits an audience, Father.
I knew de blood trolls were a threat, but I never imagined... dis...
If dat monstrosity is freed, it will mean de end of Zuldazar!
Now ya see! Now ya undahstand! G'huun gonna claim ya all!
For the Alliance.
Let's keep moving. Rakera won't survive dis desert for long.
Strength and honor. Blood and thunder.
Mere words to others... but everything to us.
We are the last survivors of a proud tribe. The uncorrupted... the unbroken... the Mag'har!
Jakra'zet is a traitor, but de king won't act without proof.
You know I must, Kaja. Duty before all else.

Text: Let them through!
Out of the way! Bringin' in the big guns!
Time to earn our pay. Fire at will!

Text1: Fools! G'huun not gonna fail! Ya power be useless!

Text: Oh! Curveball! Curveball!

Text1: Curveball! Curveball!
Princess Talanji was kind enough to inform us of an old portal network we might be able to tap into.
Oculeth, see what you can do with the portal system here. We will need supply lines to the Horde capitals.
Champion, you seem to be on the right track for gaining the trust of the Zandalari. I must attend to my other duties. Good luck.
How tenacious! Feel honor in your accomplishment of living long enough to face my pride.

Text: Alliance... hold!
No! I demand an honorable death!
My father once said that Varok Saurfang embodied the honor of the Horde...
Listen to me. There is no honor in this.
That is not for an Alliance king to decide!
At this moment, it is.
Take him to the Stockades.
When I return, we will speak of honor... and how it may yet be reclaimed.
If... you return.

Text1: Are those gunpowder shipments in from the Ashvane Foundry?

Text: Y-yes, Captain Stone.
Text1: Y-yes, Captain Stone.
Well, load them onto the ship! Those explosives are a safety hazard.

Text: Of course, Captain.
Text1: Of course, Captain.

Text: Almost dere. Dis is de island dat our scouts say holds a lot of Azerite.
We do not know what else is here, though. You have to watch your backs out dere.
Lower de gangplanks. Dis is de place.

Text1: Careful there, John. That gunpowder'll blow your hand clean off.

Text: What? This is a BOMB? I thought it was an avocado.
Sure am glad we got assigned out here today.
Text1: Sure am glad we got assigned out here today.

Text: Captain Stone's really worked up about something.
Text1: Captain Stone's really worked up about something.

Text: I heard it has something to do with all those crates we've been getting from the Ashvane.
Text1: I heard it has something to do with all those crates we've been getting from the Ashvane.
That's far enough.
Mother? Is that... you?
I'm so glad you could join us my dear. Your father has missed you so.
What... What have you done to him?!
Be appreciative, girl! Not only is your father alive and well, but he will soon be lord of all Kul Tiras! Come join us, child...

Text: Keep away from her, you heartless witch!

Text1: Why Marshal, that's no way to talk to a Lady. I should teach you some manners.
Now, Marshal, be a dear and bring Lucille to my quarters, after you dispose of these pests...
Come, Arthur.

Text: As you wish, Mother...
Pretty sure this is the place. Supposed to be a lot of Azerite around here.
You know, there could also be, like, giant spiders here, too. I'm just saying, you never know.
Bring her in, try not to hit anything. And get the gangplanks down, thanks.
Invaders in the Foundry! I repeat, INVA-
Text1: Invaders in the Foundry! I repeat, INVA-
Head into town and round up as many guards as you can!
For the Horde!
If what dis exile says is true, den you must investigate. But use caution. Jakra'zet may still be near.
The mountain gives us life. Grants us strength.
Upon hammer and anvil, our kingdom was forged. With hearts o' fire... and wills o' iron.
The same blood that flows through our veins... flows through Azeroth's as well.
This world must be defended. Forward, Dark Irons! Tae battle we march!
The town we passed by, Bridgeport, seems to be the largest threat in the area.
We need to show the Kul Tirans what it means to make an enemy of the Horde.
Come, hero. Let me show you around.
It is said de Great Seal is one of de only things still standing dat is older than de Zandalari Empire.
My father keeps many of his treasures here in de royal vault.
You can find your nightborne friend in de Hall of Ancient Paths. Come see me when you are done looking around.

Text: But do you have time to waste?

Text1: This isn't over!
Zelling! Damn you, we need you alive!

Text: <wheeze> I'm... sorry. I.. can't... I don't have anything... left in me...
Miss Voss, <cough> please... bring me back... I must help my family... I'll do anything... anything...

Text1: You'll be shunned if you become one of us. You look in a mirror and all you'll see is a monster.
We'll see. Maybe it can be different... just this one time.
Lilian Voss. Why have you called upon me?

Text: Lilian. We can find other tidesages. You know his family won't accept him.

Text1: Bring this man back. He has been chosen to become Forsaken.
As you command, by the will of the Dark Lady.

Text: Infuse this amulet with power... it might be the only way tae save her!
Finally, a challenger steps up!
How is this possible?!
This will not stand! You have not seen the last of Captain Hermes and his trio of ruthless crabs!
Looks like you need to seek some shell-ter. Get it? Shells? Crabs! Victory is mine!
Yeah! Crustacean power!
Brothers and sisters, behold our glorious destiny!
I would... damn my soul... for all eternity... if it meant my family's happiness... please! You must...
You... must...
I... I live! Hahaha! I must see Julia and the children at once. They will be delighted!

Text1: I guess we'll see what happens now.
The rumors are true. Daelin's Gate... has fallen.
A pirate fleet struck the gate with overwhelming force...

Text: Pirates?! The Proudmoores can't even protect us from pirates anymore!

Text1: For shame!
But it has not been enough.
Lady Ashvane has been my rock since those first dark days when we both lost our husbands. Now, she will be the kingdom's rock. Now... she is--
A liar!
So, this was your play all along. Despicable.
What is the meaning of this, girl?!
Lady Priscilla Ashvane, you are under arrest for trafficking, conspiring with pirates, and high treason against the Admiralty of Kul Tiras.
Your company MADE the weapons that destroyed Daelin's Gate using this!
It's called Azerite... and the Alliance and Horde are already at war over it.
You hired the pirate fleet, armed them to the teeth, and set them upon your own countrymen.
And I almost... Priscilla... How could you betray the kingdom? How could you betray me?
You're too weak to rule, Katherine.

Text: It's over, Stormsong! Look around you... You're surrounded!
All I see are lost souls, crying for release.
You brought your end with you, Pike. I must deliver the fleet to our glorious savior... Azshara.
STORMSONG!

Text1: Sam, no!
Dis ends here, General. De plots. De lies. De murders.

Text: <Jakra'zet groans.>

Text1: Give him a clean death. We have seen enough suffering for one day.

Text: Suffering? You have not seen true suffering. Not yet...
But you will!
No... It cannot be!

Text1: He was de final sacrifice... We have failed.

Text: Prepare to face my unbeatable team of highly modified and customized robots!
No pet can compete with my team, I'm unstoppable!
Inconceivable! Next time I'm building bigger robots.
My brilliant mind making even more brilliant machines is an unbeatable combination.
Malfunction!? That's not supposed to happen!

Text1: I dunnae know who that is, but I'm sure she needs killin'!

Text: Hey there, name's Dilbert McClint, Infestation Management.  Always nice to battle a fellow arachnoid enthusiast.
Yeah, that's right.  We're bad! Rock and Roll!
When one falls, another takes its place!
One guy, three spiders, 26 total legs, you didn't have a chance.
Looks like it's time for me to tear out the bad battle spiders and put in some good battle spiders.
Show dem, leader of Zandalar. Show da blade to those dat need to see it da most. Give dem peace.
Ya brought de champion to dese shores against ya father's will. Ya learned da secrets of G'huun when no one be listenin'.
Ya set in motion what be needed ta save ya people. Now, more than ever, dey be callin' for a leader dey can love and trust.
Show dem da blade. Become da symbol dey need.

Text1: Dis was not my achievement.
Behold de blood of G'huun. By his will were borne de deaths of Shadra, Hi'reek, Torga, and ...and Rezan.
By his will were borne de deaths of so many of our brothers and sisters.
Let dis glaive be displayed as a reminder dat no matter how far we fall, no matter how much we lose, we are Zandalari!$bWe adapt, we find a way to survive!
If it were not for dis hero of de Horde, our losses would have been far worse.$bDis proves, more than ever, dat it is time for us to adapt, to become part of de world again.
Zandalar forever!

Text: Brothers and sisters! The Horde is pressing further into Darkshore! Rally at the Wildbend River.

Text1: We are getting out of here!

Text: Sylvanas! Your foul deeds desecrate this sacred place! Andu-falah-dor!

Text1: Malfurion. How gracious of you to join us...
Who would have guessed that you would come to protect your precious trees?

Text: Begone, witch!

Text1: Argh! My eyes! It burns!
Where did you fly away to, little bird?

Text: Mrglrglrgl!
Text1: Mrglrglrgl!

Text: Mrgl? Rgl!
Text1: Mrgl? Rgl!

Text: Mrg? Grml?!
Text1: Mrg? Grml?!

Text: Rgrml grml grml!
Text1: Rgrml grml grml!

Text: Mrglrgl? Mrg! Rgl!
Text1: Mrglrgl? Mrg! Rgl!

Text: Mrrrmgrl!
Text1: Mrrrmgrl!

Text: Rgl... mrg...
Text1: Rgl... mrg...

Text: Mrg!
Text1: Mrg!

Text: Grgl...
Text1: Grgl...

Text: Rgll mgrgl... rgl...
Text1: Rgll mgrgl... rgl...

Text: Mrrg mrgl?
Text1: Mrrg mrgl?

Text: Mrglrggg...
Text1: Mrglrggg...
Katherine Proudmoore has spent her life doing what's best for Kul Tiras!
My dear friend Priscilla and I have discussed this. I believe that what is best for Kul Tiras is that I step down as Lord Admiral...
I will shoulder this heavy burden. I can only hope I will be a worthy successor.
And we have evidence!
Your family has always been too weak.
The Proudmoore legacy of failure dies with you!
OUTRIGGERS! OPEN FIRE!
Look! They're withdrawing!
You think your pets have a chance against my Azerite infused team? You wish!
Can't say I'm surprised, my team is clearly the best.
But my pets are infused with Azerite! It's what pets crave!
Score one for team Fizzie!
That was my least favorite of the bunch, time to play with the real hard hitters, get ready!

Text: Just remember as we start this battle, you asked for this.
Bees are clearly superior. This proves it.
Not my bees! No!
Score one for the bees!
Every time I train up new bees, it's always the same thing. They get big and strong and seemingly unbeatable, and then they sting something and die.

Text1: I've found the toughest sea creatures around to battle for me, you don't stand a chance.
Never a doubt in my mind.
Always more fish in the ocean, right?  Maybe that's not what that saying means now that I think about it.
Looks like that one now sleeps with the fishes!
You're better suited to be chum on a fishing boat than battling for my team.
Strange creatures on this island will make for a strange battle I suspect.
You need much more training before you can handle a master like myself.
This was not supposed to happen, the prophecy spoke otherwise.
Return to where you came from!
Your determination is admirable, but the outcome of this has already been determined.

Text: If you want to beat the likes of me you're going to need a bigger boat to haul these out of here.
One person against one shark, maybe an even fight.  One person against three? You're insane.
Big deal you beat me. I'm still stuck down here for eternity. At least I had a conversation today.
Feeding time, boys!
The smell of blood in the water will just attract more sharks.

Text1: Before we start, I just want to remind you to not feel too bad when my team annihilates yours.
Like I said in the beginning, my team is clearly superior.
Well this is most unexpected. You can bet I will be ready to win the next time we meet.
Annihilated!
Unexpected.

Text: These little guys are pretty strange, but they sure pack a punch. Are you sure you want this fight?
They have a lot of sharp pointy things and look mean, and you thought you could win?
I should diversify my roster of pets now that I think about it.  Three of the same kind of pet, what was I thinking?
Burly's Pet Battle Training Center.  I like the sound of that, and now I'm one step closer to beating you!
This is not the way this is supposed to be going. I'm supposed to be winning!

Text1: We did it...  We actually did it!
Still, they could be back. And if they bring those guns to bear on Boralus...

Text: You trespass upon sacred ground.
What do we call you now?
Do you not understand?
and you have no place among kings.

Text1: You will not escape your crimes any longer.
Dis. Ends. Now.

Text: Designation: G'huun.
Scans indicate Nazmir and Vol'dun devices currently inoperable. Last functioning seal: Zuldazar.

Text1: If de last seal is destroyed, dat monster will be unleashed upon Azeroth!
Ya fight be hopeless... G'huun gonna be free!
Once Zandalar lies in ruins, da empire of da Old Gods be risin' again!

Text:
You're helping de princess. Dat's good. You keep doing dat. Destroy de blood troll threat before it consumes us all.

De person you want to speak with is at de Zul'jan Ruins. Her name is Provisioner Lija. She will help you with what you need.
Text1:
You're helping de princess. Dat's good. You keep doing dat. Destroy de blood troll threat before it consumes us all.

De person you want to speak with is at de Zul'jan Ruins. Her name is Provisioner Lija. She will help you with what you need.
Lets fight with honor, stranger.
Do not be sad about defeat, learn from your mistakes and rise up to the challenge.
I will train and be prepared for the next time we meet.
Hah! Got one!
When one falls in battle, the others gain strength to fight even harder.

Text: Time to get down and battle! Lets do this!
Another win for the best team, me!
I hate losing! I'll be stronger next time, you can count on that.
Another one bites the dust.
You monster! That was my favorite pet.
This place is spooky, lets make this a quick battle.
It was a good fight, but you're no match for me.
This place is cursed, I never lose that badly.
You had best take care of that before it's used for some blood ritual.
That pet was a little creepy anyway, no big loss.
Time for a great adventure!
I won? Excellent, I'll tell all my friends about this!
Shucks, I hate losing.  Good fight.
Good fight little guy, you'll get better!
Time to farm up some more pet bandages.
I always appreciate a good battle with a new challenger.
With some extra practice you'd be a great challenge for even myself, keep at it.
Astounding, I haven't lost a match in years.  Well fought!
Victory is within my grasp, I can almost feel it.
Do not cower in the face of defeat, rise up to the challenge if you can.

Text1: I'm on a winning streak, you have no chance against me and my team.
Hooray, my winning streak increases!
This doesn't really count as a loss, I'm keeping my win streak.
Looks like my win streak is about to increase.
I wasn't ready, this doesn't count!
I have not battled in a long while, I hope I am still a good challenge to you.
My goodness, I guess I had a stronger team than I realized.
I guess I may be out of practice.
Do not be sad about losing that one, your other pets look plenty strong.
Do not worry little one, I will take care of you.
The critters in this land are vicious, I hope you're ready for this.
Like I said, the critters in this land are vicious.  Good fight either way.
I need more time to train with these new species, I will be stronger when we next battle.
That's probably going to leave a scar.
Maybe this isn't the strongest new species out here, I should keep looking for better things to capture.
You come to face me in my own home? Good luck.
Looks like I have an advantage on my home turf.
This is most unexpected, I will win next time we meet, stranger.
The species of Zandalar are unrivaled in power, your other pets stand no chance.
My pets only grow stronger when an ally falls in battle.
I don't know what to do, Daelin. I don't know what to believe in... who to trust.
Priscilla, the greatest friend of my heart... has stabbed me in it.
I have nothing... no one... left...

Text: You have Jaina.

Text1: Jaina betrayed the kingdom.

Text: Jaina did nothing but follow her heart. And she's suffered for that.
... she's suffering even more now. Isn't she?

Text1: ... I see her... in my dreams.
Genn... She's burning.

Text: Katherine, she's calling out to you... You must go to her.

Text1: It's too late for that.

Text: If you can hear her... then it's not too late.
I would give anything to hold my boy again.
You've been given one more chance.
Take it. Bring her home.
He admired you for that, and so do I.

Text1: If you want a job done right... use bigger explosives!

Text: May the Light bless the spirits of our ancestors, for they've chosen to allow my son to rest upon this holy ground.
It is here, surrounded by the heroes and patriots of Gilneas where he belongs.
We'll return, Liam.  I swear this to you.

Text1: You were a true man of the people, Liam.  Unlike any Royal I ever met.  We'll make them pay for this.

Text: Gilneas will remember your courage forever, Liam.

Text1: No one rides the Lady!
No, no, silly $r...

Text: Attack!
How many coconuts can we get for the ugly one?
THREE? He woulda paid five, easy... Dummy!

Text1: Vol'jin, son of Sen'jin, once warchief of the Horde... Hear my voice and appear before us.

Text: Talanji. Ya voice be a mighty one.
Vol'jin! Is it really you, my old friend?
Baine... ya heart beats strong and true... just like ya fadda. I be glad da demons didn't take ya.
Sylvanas led us to victory in the war against the Legion.
But since then... she has done much to strain the honor that binds the Horde together.
I must know... when the voice spoke to you, bidding you to name her warchief... what spirit was it?
Ah, my young friend. Death be... dark. Me memory... not be what it once was.
Was it Bwonsamdi? Did he crave the death she would bring?
Da memory, it be denied me by da shadows. Shadows... dat... dat be comin' for ya! Watch out!
You're the last of your tribe with any sense left.  As a reward for giving us Prince Nadun, I grant you the gift that is your birthright and more!
Your makers failed you... your flawed race succumbed to the curse of flesh!  Lord Deathwing's gift makes you perfect again!
I remember dyin'. I remember glimpsin' da Other Side.
I was expectin' ta see ol' Bwonsamdi, or Shadra, or Hir'eek... any of da loa.
Dere was a presence. Somethin' movin' in da shadows. Somethin' powerful.
Sometin' not be right dat day. Da demons, deir blades slipped past me guard.
Like dey be doin' now. Cannot hear dem, champion. Da voices of da loa be silent.
I been callin' ta Bwonsamdi for a long time. He not be hearin' me... or he be choosin' not ta answer.
I remember it takin' me somewhere, but da memory of where be hidden from me. Ta keep me from sharin' da truth...
Da truth dat it might not be da loa who wanted Sylvanas to be warchief, but somethin' far more powerful.
Ahhhh, ya come back. Did ya find da spirit of Vol'jin? Or ya here ta make a deal?

Text1: Loa of death, your servant Vol'jin has called to you. Yet you have turned a deaf ear to his pleas.

Text: What? Nonono. Ya be mistaken, Talanji.
Speak plainly! Was it you who urged Vol'jin to name Sylvanas warchief?
Mind ya tone, bull-mon... or ya be talkin' with ya father soon enough.
Why would me want da Banshee Queen in charge? Nononono. Sure, I be all for war and death, but dat Sylvanas... she be tippin' da scales too far.
Balance be important! Besides, dat one got a nasty habit of keepin' what she kills. No, ya warchief be no friend to ol' Bwonsamdi.
Lich King. Da voice I heard as I be dyin'... tellin' me to name Sylvanas warchief... was it yours?
The Banshee Queen's schemes threaten the balance. I had no hand in them.
And me spirit bein' trapped in dis world... is dat your doin'?
Vol'jin... your soul has walked on the Other Side and returned. You have been altered... more than you know.
Is it you who be trappin' me soul in dis world? Ta jail me like ya jail da Scourge?
You are neither undead nor damned. You do not belong here. Leave this place at once.

Text1: I do not like de look of dis. I suggest we go... quickly!

Text: Leave now or stay forever. The choice is yours.

Text1: Minions of the Banshee Queen, leave this place or die.

Text1: We must all do our part.

Text:
I oversee all war-related construction.

I vow we will recover Teldrassil before the war is over. But we face dwindling resources and rising casualties. If I can ask your patience for a while longer--

Text1: Thank the sands you're here. There's nothing quite right about this at all!

Text:
Greetings, $p.

Iltheux has put me in charge of the vintage. I decide what goes in the wine to make it palatable for the Horde.

Text1:
Look at Kazit, workin' so hard.

Text: I'm gathering ingredients for the wine, but it's a tiring job. I think I'll just take another quick break...

I look forward to helping in any way I can.

Text1: I really am, aren't I? Tellin' this one what to do 'aint as easy as it looks!
You got it! I'll send Kazit out to find whatever ingredients ya need.

Text: That sounds wonderful! I do love working with food and drink.

Text1: Whatever ya need, we got it.

Text: Kiro. I must apologize for so hastily dismissing you earlier.
The Horde endures because we band together in times of adversity.
Though I turned you away, you selflessly came to our aid. Just as you did in Vol'dun.
Such is the true spirit of the Horde. If you still desire to join us, you would be most welcome within our ranks.
[DNT] For a moment I forgot this.
[DNT] Burdened by the troubles facing our new allies, I turned you away.
[DNT] Even still, you worked to lessen the strain, without being asked.
It would be our honor, High Chieftain.
Then it is decided. From this day forth, the vulpera of Vol'dun are allies of the Horde!

Text1: They don't eat alpacas here, right?

With ancient words, I invoke your most ruthless phase.
With this offering, I demand to wear your darkest face.
Elune! Make me the instrument of your vengeance!
Now, we shall have justice. The Night Warrior lives... within me.

Text1: Annihilated

Text: If we are to push further into Azshara's realm and obtain the Tidestone, we will need to know the lay of the land.

Text1: Obtaining the Tidestone must be our top priority. But it would be unwise to press further into Azshara's realm without first knowing what we're up against.

Text: Hold onto the gryphons, they're trained to avoid all sorts of danger. Hopefully it also includes fire from a dragon's artifact!
I'm gonna get meself to Camp Bronzebeard te see how they're doin'. I'll meet up with the rest of ye later!
We'll have to leap off the gryphons when we get to the camp and get to work as fast as possible with whoever is left there.
I'm goin' ahead te make sure Camp Bronzebeard is safe. For the Alliance!
The recruits back at Stormwind are never going to believe this!
Let's hope whoever has the shield up lets us in, or this will be one short ride!
Hang on!
Deal, now hold on tight!
Not if I can help it, ye overgrown lizard!
We'll hold the dragon's attention! Ye best get te Camp Bronzebeard, they need yer help!

Text1: So be it.
Evaluation: Possible to reverse condition by amplifying Heart of Azeroth.
Collection of these essences necessary to fortify Heart of Azeroth--and its wielder.

Text: Are ye ready, champion?
Jaina...?
You found one of my hidden treasures! It's trapped of course, I'm no fool.

Text1: Behold the wonders of Nazjatar.
Amazing!

Text: Welcome to the jam!
Yeah! Get dunked on!
MALOWNED!
You challenge me in my own city? Laughable!
Ouch! That stung.
All according to plan.
I will remember this when we meet again.
There we go! Ye can use that console tae connect us tae the Chamber of Heart.

Text1: Remote link established. Awaiting circuit completion.

Text: Move along, let the real challengers step up.
Hold yer horses, lass. This thing didn't exactly come with instructions.
Wait... it all makes sense now! Connectin' the power circuit!
What's this? Interestin'... I'll remember that fer later.

Text1: Acknowledged. Rerouting power to Forge of Origination.

Text: For all my brilliance, even I never could figure out how to unlock this one. A pity, you may as well not even bother with it.
Impressive! Most impressive!
You defeated my lock! Unbelievable!
My lock, defeated? Well, this was one of my more 'basic' models.
Enjoy your success, looter. My other treasures are far more secure.
Haha! You'll never steal my treasures!
Don't feel bad, you never had a chance.
Begone, looter!
[DNT] I know of your kind. Your people aided the Horde with our efforts on Zandalar.
[DNT] Please, come forward. What can I do for you?
[DNT] I do not disagree, but taking on new allies now, when we cannot address the needs of our current allies would be unwise.
Sasha's snout says this is the place. Maybe they're in one of these houses?
Let's get moving. The peons can't be far.
Head inside and check things out. I'll keep watch.
We will take your soul, and raise the dragon from the dead!
The full force of the Alliance will rain down upon you!
As a newly arrived soul you should know this is a place of torment and of penance.
Not to fear though, for as you see by these many sinstones, the road to redemption is possible.

Text1: Let's go. Those monsters have my son.

Text: Henry? I didn't see him... but I'm sure he's still alive.
Each of these sinstones represents a soul who has come to this place and cleansed themselves of their sins, eventually moving on from here or accepting the role of a venthyr.
Final judgement comes from the Master. It is he who commands this place. It is he who embraces souls to become venthyr, the tormentors and eaters of sin.
There are always those few who are unwilling to work for redemption.
Or don't agree with their sinstone.
Or are simply just a bunch of bad apples.
Thems get the boot. Down to the Maw and never to come back. Take this poor soul for example. He's on his final warning.
Won't even admit he did somethin' wrong. Still thinks he's someone important.
Hold, creatures. This is a guest, not a charge.
Quick, make yaself presentable. Lord Chamberlain is here.
Mother... I'm sorry. I tried to fight the ogres... but they were too strong.

Text1: Henry... always remember that you are more than your mistakes. Now, Private Garrick, I want a full situation report.

Text: Yes, mother--Captain Garrick! The ogres are using necromancy to raise a dragon from the dead.
They need sacrifices like us to fuel their magic. They're about to start a ritual that--
It's already begun... they're going to use the life force they gathered to reanimate the dragon!
That's far enough, orc! Dismount and submit or die!
Text1: That's far enough, orc! Dismount and submit or die!
Out of our way, fools!

Text: My children, I know the suffering you have endured.
The shortage of anima and the lack of new souls have inflicted terrible hardship upon us all.
I fear further sacrifices must be made if Revendreth is to survive this crisis.
Ah! The mortal who escaped the inescapable prison. A living soul restoring hope to the realms eternal.
This drought has left my people desperate...
But if you were to aid our cause, then I could gratefully provide the aid you seek.
Begging my Master's pardon.
Ravagers and thieves. Stop them before they raid what few anima reserves we have left.

Text1: Elune, please shield us from harm!

Text: As one of the mightiest human kingdoms, Stormwind upholds an enduring tradition of brave knights and legendary heroes.
Representing the stout and enduring dwarves of Ironforge, you have emerged from the mountain and stand ready to face any challenge.
As one of the ancient and elusive night elves, you have ventured forth from the sacred forests to aid your allies and protect the wilds.
Though small in stature, as a gnome your unrivaled ingenuity and fierce determination allow you to stand tall beside your allies.
Fleeing a distant world overcome by demonic corruption, you and your fellow draenei have secured a new home among steadfast allies.
Like many pandaren, you have known a life of harmony on the traveling isle of Shen-zin Su. But your intrepid spirit yearns for adventure.
Though the worgen curse ravaged your home kingdom of Gilneas, you have mastered your feral rage as a weapon against your rivals.
Find the lost expedition members and bring them home. For the Alliance!
[DNT] Why don't the sin'dorei get their hands dirty?
[DNT] You should be rewarded for a hard day's work!
When I'm warchief, peons will be respected members of the Horde!
I'll make my way back to Crushblow and get things cooking.

Text1: Let's get to work!

Text: [DEPRECATED] You two, dredgers, leave that mortal alone. They are under the protection of the Master.
Come, mortal, let us away from this place.
No doubt by now you have heard of the anima drought plaguing our reality.
[DEPRECATED] My Master, the supreme Sire Denathrius, has a plan to see us through these dark times.
We face this challenge with dignity and remain united behind the Master. Revendreth remains resolute!
They claim he is hoarding aether when in fact he must ration what limited reserves we have left.
Rumors of a rebellion are greatly overstated. Everything is under control.
Lord Chamberlain! There's a commotion up ahead. Looks like a fight.
Rebels. Just drive either over or through them. They would not dare to-  Aah!
Aaaaaaaah!
Aaaaaaaaah!
Aaaaaaaah!
He is your Master too, traitor! Release us at once.
As you command, Lord Chamberlain.

Text1: Don't get lazy on me, Kazit!
Nothing wrong with positive reinforcement, but...
Hmm, I don't know if that's the best use of Mida's talents...
Seems like a good fit! Goblins can acquire anything, at any time.
While words of encouragement are always welcome...
Uh, are you sure about that? Have you seen the size of his hooves?
Wise choice. Highmountain Tauren are really strong!
You did see him sleeping, right?
More like sleeping on the fruit...
Good call. Nomi is well known for his culinary creations.
Let's tell the vintner about the changes we've made.
Meet you back in the big city!
No need to wait for me, $p. I'll make my way back to Orgrimmar once I've fed Dolly and Dot.

Text: [DNT] Small problems grow and fester if not addressed.
[DNT] Without your assistance, our troubles might have consumed us.
[DNT] We need allies willing to tackle issues head-on, no matter the size.
[DNT] If you still wish to join our ranks, you would be most welcome within the Horde.

Text1: Am I glad to see you! These naga are relentless.
Time for us to get outta here. See you back in Orgrimmar.
Why don't the Horde want us?
Sure is good to be out of the sand.
So we'll need to prove ourselves to the Horde? That shouldn't be a problem.

Text: I never like turning anyone away, but I could not agree to add to our ranks when so many within the Horde are struggling.
I'd say we're making progress, $p.

Text1: If we wanna stop the naga, we need to take down their leader's shield. I'm counting on you!
Let's enjoy this moment together.

Text: ARF! <bzzzt>
You win!
Text1: You win!
I've been expecting you.
Come, let us find a more comfortable place to chat.
No need to be on edge. As you can see, my guards have been instructed to treat you as a guest.

Text: Since bein' wounded by the Mad Titan, Azeroth has been cryin' out in pain. In her hour o' need, she lent you her power.
Today, at long last, she's free from the grasp o' the Old Gods. Her song rings clear and strong throughout this chamber.
Hold her heart with pride. Know that ye are more than a champion of yer people... ye are a champion of Azeroth!
We vulpera have always been resourceful. No matter the adversity, we do what it takes to survive... and keep our family strong.
The Horde helped us when we needed it, and now it's time to return the favor. A fair trade, if you ask me.
A whole world of adventure is awaiting you out there. Explore it and become a hero.
We mechagnomes spent years in isolation, tirelessly enhancing our bodies and minds.
Now we realize that balance is the key to happiness.
It is time to leave Mechagon and rejoin our gnomish cousins.
We have to do what we can to appease the peons.

Text1: UNUSED
They're the best 'pacas in all the land!

Text: Constructs! Hold this ground! Our victory is at hand!
Text1: Constructs! Hold this ground! Our victory is at hand!
Out of the way, little spiders!
These poor creatures... we cannot stop to help them.
By the Light, you're alive!

Text: Ye did a good job, savin' those people and dealin' with those spiders.

Text1: Those spiders were victims, too. They just lost their home.

Text: Yeah... well, I guess ye could see it that way.

Text1: The Light shines on all creatures. That does not mean I have to like them.

Text: This mortal will not become another puppet of the Master.

Text1: You have achieved much in the span of a mortal life. We are fortunate to call you an ally.
And so by anima, we bless you. By spirit, we embrace you. By oath, we stand beside you.
[DNT] By oath, we stand beside you.
Rise, $p of Azeroth, as huntsman of the Wild Hunt, champion of the Court of Night, and protector of Ardenweald.

Text: Hah! Our dragon will crush them!

Text1: Initiating query for suitable alternatives. Standby...

Text: The Alliance has sent word. They have agreed to the armistice. This bitter war is finally over.
At last we can begin to heal our wounded Earth Mother... and the wounded Horde as well.
One question remains. Who will serve as warchief? Perhaps, you, Thrall, would--
No. I told Saurfang I would not lead the Horde again.
But perhaps the question is not who should become warchief... but whether there should be one at all.
Though the Horde has changed through the years--for good or ill--we have always looked to a warchief to guide us forward.
That legacy must end. The war nearly cost us everything. There is no place for a warchief in a time of peace.
It is true--the Horde has changed. Our ranks have grown, and new voices have stepped forth to lead.
This is what makes us strong. All of us, building a new future--together.
The armistice is signed. At long last, the Fourth War is over.

Text1: No. Not while the Black Moon still cries out for vengeance. Not until the Horde has answered for its treachery.

Text: Further bloodshed will not bring back the fallen. We must renew our hope and forge a future for those who survived.

Text1: And when the next warchief musters an army, will hope save you if it is Stormwind that burns?

Text: I know it's difficult to trust, but there are signs of change within the Horde.

Text1: Your faith is naive, lion son. I will sign no treaty unless it is written in the Banshee's blood!

Text: There is truth in her words, Anduin.
When that day comes, no scrap of parchment will hold them back.
The path to peace will not be easy, and not all will choose to walk it.
It has to.
I have been training pets longer than almost any other living being. Do not underestimate me.
My tactics and strategy are unmatched. Do not feel bad when you inevitably lose.
A lucky strike, my retaliation will be swift.
You did not stand a chance, my pets are top tier.
Astonishing! Perhaps there are still some tricks I can learn.
Calculations complete, victory is guaranteed.
How did you plan on winning? I know all of your moves, I'm practically cheating.
Inconceivable! I'm not worried, this is all still part of my great plan. Just wait and see, your doom is impending.
Calculated.
Whether I win or lose, I hope it's quick.
Finally, maybe I can take a vacation now.
Whatever, I'm tired of all of this work.
Finally, something is going the way I want it to.
That wasn't even my strongest pet. You'll be sorry for that.

Text1: It's time to crush some skulls!
I told you I am the strongest and that I would crush you, so I did.
Looks like my pets need to train as much as I do.
Yeah, CRUSHED!
My sweet pet! I will avenge you!
We meet in battle at last. Feel the wrath of the COUNCIL OF CHAOS!
I must admit, I'm disappointed. You meddled in our affairs so much, and yet you are defeated so easily.
It appears I have greatly underestimated you.
Our victory is imminent, our plans about to unfold!
We will not fail, that is merely a small setback.
Neural link at maximum strength, time to unleash some mayhem!
My genius is unmatched, my greatest creation cannot be stopped!
Years of planning and work and masterful engineering, now just a pile of scrap. My next project is starting with a giant laser instead of all of this random junk.
WOW! Power spike!

Text: But this relentless quest for perfection nearly brought us to ruin.
We can improve ourselves without losing our individuality in the process.
Together, we will forge a brighter future. For the Alliance!
I shall tear this world apart!
No more excuses. The Master will have his tithe of anima or I will see to it that everyone in this miserable hamlet are exiled to the Ember Ward.
There, the link is up.
For the vulpera... and for the Horde!
In place of a warchief, there is now a council led by Baine, Thrall, and the others. I believe they can--
But this is the only way to build a better future. I believe it will work, Genn.
Peace may be on the table today, but soon enough the Horde will sound their drums and march for war.
Shattered!
Text1: Shattered!
This place already feels like home.

Text: In these moments of calm, I can't help but wonder what new adventures await.
RUN!!!
Dead end! Well, time to see if this amulet works.
Master! Master! The creature has arrived!

Text1: I know. I raised him to overcome any challenge.

Text: We have other rituals to oversee. Savor the final moments of your life!

Text1: Then we need to move quickly. Recruit, Private Garrick, the Alliance never gives up hope, even in the face of disaster.
We'll put a stop to these rituals before the ogres can complete them. Let's go!

Text: My Prince!
Theotar! My old friend. I am so happy to see you. And I see you managed to get your shirt off...
You as well. I could grate carrots on those ribs of yours.
I sent out the call to any who survived. We have quite a gathering collecting here.

Text1: Renathal.

Text: Accuser. Thank you for sending this Maw Walker to find us.

Text1: Curator...
I am fine. I will be fine.

Text: My liege.
Draven! This is more than I could have hoped for. Report.
At Theotar's request, we moved what remains of our forces here to Sinfall.
There are far less of us than we had in our last assault.
Gather the forces, we attack soon. I have a plan, but we must act swiftly before Denathrius learns of my escape.

Text: With the medallions combined, we can seize control of Revendreth.
The bargain between Denathrius and the Jailer will leave us all to be consumed by the Maw.
I want our ways to survive. If that makes me selfish, I would hope you are all selfish as well.
You mean YOU could seize control. These are merely the ravings of a selfish prince desperate to reclaim his former glory.

Text1: None of your grand words matter. You cannot defeat both the Jailer and the Master.
But I must agree with the others. You lack... leverage.

Text: I've heard enough. This usurper demands our medallions but offers nothing.

Text1: I will not subject my stoneborn children to further suffering.
Why Renathal, if only you had shown such passion ages ago! I find it positively enthralling.

Text: Foolish loa! Ya don't be stoppin' me power. First I be feastin' on ya followers... den you!
Hah! I be callin' da shots now! So ya better start tellin' me all da bad, bad things ya done ta Ardenweald.
Feh! Me no bow down ta ya cheap tricks!
Tsk. Such a grumpy loa! I... said... SPEAK!
ARGH! Ya be too late! Me gave an ancient spirit da chance ta be joinin' me. Dey made a baaaaaad choice, and now dey be trapped in da Maw!
Ya don't say? Well, good ting me got a deal with dis mortal who gonna jump in dat bad ol' place... and be gettin' out again!
Ya don't be stoppin' da Jailer! Him be workin' his plans for a long time. A looooooong time.
War been burnin' dis whole world ta ashes... all over one... little... whisper ta dis foolish troll.
Dat voice... whisperin' as da poison be burnin' in me veins... Windrunner...
Oh, ya like me whispers, little chieftain? Was gonna send ya soul to da Maw meself... but ya bond ta dis world be too hard ta break.
Ya be borin' us, Mueh'zala! Time for ya to go back to da Other Side.
Don't ya worry though! Ya got yaself a new master...
Ya ol' friend Bwonsamdi.
Bwonsamdi! Ya be too important ta summon me yaself?
I gonna loose da bindin' on Mueh'zala now. Ya best be makin' sure me people don't be lost ta his power.
Tink ya breakin' free now, Mueh'zala? Hmph.
It be me who named Sylvanas warchief. But Mueh'zala and da Jailer... dey be pullin' da strings all along.
Den how 'bout we get a little payback, hmm? Rescue dat ancient spirit from da Maw... and bring it nice and safe to da Winter Queen.
Wait, $n. I got somethin' ta say.
Hey dere, ya majesty! Ya ol' friend Bwonsamdi be helpin' dis one find alla dem missin' loa.

Text1: I will take these three spirits into our care, Bwonsamdi.
Along with this other. Intriguing... a mortal soul entwined with the essence of a loa.
I cannot say what fate will befall you, Vol'jin of the Darkspear. But I offer you this chance to one day be reborn anew.

Text: I be deeply honored, ya majesty. $p, thank ya for all ya done for me... in life, and in death.
Hmm, Rezan be smarter dan I thought! Maybe one day dere gonna be a new loa makin' deals with ol' Bwonsamdi, hm?

Text1: As I explained before, Sire, we cannot rush such a delicate process.

Text: Our friend grows... impatient.

Text1: But master, I--

Text: Well, what have we here?

Text1: Sire?

Text: My defiant accuser and her hapless mortal pawn.

Text1: You deprive your own people of anima and inflict a drought upon all of the Shadowlands!

Text: The other realms would squander our most precious resource. That won't do.
Rest assured, this anima will serve a higher purpose.

Text1: I will deal with them, sire... harshly.

Text: Of course you will.
You are a soldier of the mighty Horde, a disparate band of races united in their pursuit of freedom, honor, and glory.
A Horde expedition sent to explore an uncharted island has recently gone missing.
As a bold new recruit, you have joined a rescue mission departing from Orgrimmar.
Though the orcs came to this world seeking conquest, your people now stand proudly among its greatest champions.
The undead Forsaken may be shunned by the living, but your people strive to rise above the ruins of the past and forge a new future.
As one of the wise and noble tauren, your physical might and spiritual resolve honor the legacy of your ancestors.
Renouncing the brutality of other troll tribes, you and your fellow Darkspear protect your allies with cunning ferocity.
Though the blood elf homeland was nearly lost to tragedy and betrayal, your people have reclaimed your birthright and seek a brighter destiny.
As members of the Bilgewater Cartel, you and your fellow goblins have sided with the Horde for the promise of adventure... and profit!
Find the lost expedition members and bring them home. For the Horde!

Text1: Rise, $p of Azeroth, as huntress of the Wild Hunt, champion of the Court of Night, and protector of Ardenweald.

Text: Every attendant in Oribos is taught that the Maw is unbreachable. That the malevolent souls within were sealed away for all eternity.

Text1: This mortal's escape might mean the prison is... weakening. If true, the Banished One could...
Kah-Delen! Kah-Sher! Purpose be praised! At long last, the Arbiter has stirred!

Text: More outsiders! What have you done, mortal?
Be at ease. I am Bolvar Fordragon. These knights and I are here to help.

Text1: The touch of the Maw is upon their souls as well.
As the Arbiter's voice, I heed the call of the Eternal Ones. How may I serve?
The Maw grows, surging with power! How did this come to pass?!
The evil we believed forever bound has conspired to distract and divide us.
The Primus realized the truth, but his warning came too late. I fear he paid a grave price for this knowledge.
You speak for Revendreth? Where is your sire? Where is our brother Denathrius?

Text: My sire... has betrayed us all.
The drought was his doing. He stole the very lifeblood of our realms, starving his own people... and yours as well.
When his lies were exposed, Denathrius unleashed his vast coffers of anima into the Maw... to fuel the might of his true master.

Text1: Long ago, we stood as one to imprison that... monster.
With the Primus gone and Denathrius a traitor, our pantheon has been broken... and doom comes for the Shadowlands.

Text: There is yet hope. This mortal saved me from the Maw and revealed the sire's treachery.

Text1: They aided my forest as well. Their kind has shown great potential. If focused, it could turn the tide in our favor.
Agreed. For the good of the Shadowlands, each mortal must choose a covenant.
And when our realms have regained their strength, we will stand together against the darkness.
I will see it done, Eternal Ones. With her voice have I spoken.
Come, mortal. The hour of decision is at hand.

Text: What in the name of the Master?

Text1: Anima harvesting demands finesse.

Text: See it done, Inerva.
You really must be more vigilant about uninvited guests, my lady.
... if a tad inconvenient.
But I fear you will not survive to witness the glory to come.
I humbly present... the Maw Walker.
Maw Walker, I am aware of your urgent request for anima. Under normal circumstances, I would of course oblige.
Sadly, you arrive in the midst of a violent rebellion. Our resources are stretched perilously thin.
...starving...
...and some, even defiant.

Text1: You will enjoy my hospitality, so long as you remain receptive to what I have to say.
We move, now. Those monsters have my daughter.
Cowards! Soon you will face the full might of the Horde!

Text: Yes... Yes! Bonds weakening...
A taste... of freedom. A place to start.

Text1: Mother... I tried to stop the ogres on my own. But I failed. My strength was not enough.
Shuja, the Horde is strong not when we fight alone, but when we stand united. Now, tell me what's happened here.
As you command. The ogres are using necromancy to raise a dragon from the dead.
They need sacrifices like us to fuel their magic. They're about to start a ritual that will --
It's already begun. They're going to use the life force they've gathered to reanimate the dragon!
Then we must take action. Remember that when we band together, the Horde can conquer any challenge.
We will bring an end to these rituals before the ogres can complete them. Lok-tar ogar!
An'she, watch over and protect us!
Dark magic has brought ruin to this place.
Oh good, you made it out.
Ya did good savin' da survivors an' killin' da spiders.
Those spiders had their rightful home destroyed. They deserved better.
You cannot win this battle, necromancer! Our courage never falters!

Text: My paragon, you do not stand alone!
For the Archon! For Bastion!
Ah, just the vessel I require.

Text1: Thanikos!

Text: What... are you... doing to me?!
No! No! NO!
Y-yes... master...
I have perfected you. Now serve me by destroying our enemies!
Clear the arena! The final clash is about to begin!
A victor emerges!
Text1: A victor emerges!
Look closer, Gharmal.

Text: Sin'dane, is this the meddler who thwarted our attack?
Text1: Sin'dane, is this the meddler who thwarted our attack?
The very one.

Text: So this mortal witnessed your treachery!
Your houses invaded Bastion--an act that betrays everything the Primus stood for!
The Primus is long gone, Krexus!
Text1: The Primus is long gone, Krexus!

Text: We are meant to defend the Shadowlands, not conquer it!

Text1: I think not, Krexus. Your blade... shall be broken.
Slay them all.

Text: Chosen! To arms!
Magnificent. Bron's strength is my strength. Our strength!

Text1: What was that?
Centurions will overwhelm us!

Text: Not to worry! I know what to do.
Everyone, hop on!
Recent events require us to expedite our efforts.
It is impressive that you discovered our little secret...

Text1: Why?
It seems you have an eye for talent, Warlord Grimaxe.
Hah! The rest of those ogres are running fer the hills! They never stood a chance!
In time, the island will heal from their dark rituals.
A true testament to the strength of the Alliance. Maybe you'll captain one, some day.
Come on, recruits. Let's go home.
[DNT] We need to do something!

Text: Centurions! Advance! Destroy the intruders!
But where are their banners?
Text1: But where are their banners?

Text: Where is your hunger for glory?
Text1: Where is your hunger for glory?

Text: You will recall your forces... or you will answer to my blade!
Which house do they fight for?
Text1: Which house do they fight for?
We have a living mortal in our midst. Intriguing...

Text: Or has the House of the Chosen lost its appetite?
Text1: Or has the House of the Chosen lost its appetite?

Text: Stormwind City. Capital of the noble Alliance.
Though they hail from many different lands, the races of the Alliance convene in Stormwind on matters of trade and diplomacy.
Their age-old enemy, the savage Horde, poses an ever-present threat.
But no matter the challenge, the soldiers of Stormwind stand ready to face it.
As you triumphantly return from Exile's Reach, new adventures await on the horizon.
Azeroth faces countless threats. Bold heroes are needed to rise up and defend her.
For the Alliance!
Please help Niya!
Text1: Please help Niya!
Keep running!

Text: Niya is still back there!
Text1: Niya is still back there!
The ward has been sabotaged, as we agreed.
Good. Our allies are eager to strike.
The kyrian temples will fall, and the Archon's reign shall be ended!

Text: It will take more than courage to save you now.

Text1: We can't get away! Brace yourself!

Text: To think those brutes could wield such magic. If only I had more time to study it!

Text1: I am glad that you do not. This island must be allowed to heal.
Look, $p, on the horizon. One of our gunships!
An impressive display of the Horde's strength. Those ogres would do well to run and hide.
Come, recruits. It is time we return to our home.

Text: Orgrimmar. Bulwark of the mighty Horde.
Standing as a symbol of pride and resilience, it is here that its citizens gather to barter goods and muster their strength.
Their longtime rival, the imperious Alliance, poses a relentless threat.
But no foe can hope to stand against the fearless soldiers of the Horde!
After proving your mettle on Exile's Reach, a lifetime of adventure and glory awaits.
Azeroth faces countless threats. Bold heroes are needed to rise up and defend her.
For the Horde!

Text1: Look, on the horizon! One of our airships approaches!
The Heart of the Forest is vital to Ardenweald... and to the protection of the realms beyond.
The drought has caused the Heart to wither. Its strength must be bolstered... though we have precious little anima to save our waning groves.
An impossible choice. Yet, one that must be made for the good of the cycle.

Text: Struggle all you like, mortals. You cannot escape your fate!

Text1: A true testament to the strength of the Alliance.

Text: Take our stag and ride with us, $p.
The Blighted stand in our path!
Run them down!
The Wild Hunt will cull you from Ardenweald!
Come, we ride for Hibernal Hollow.
[DEPRECATED] Niya, was it? Tell me more about this wildseed.

Text1: Thank you for escorting us, Ara'lon. It puts me at ease to know we are protected by a fierce huntsman.
[DEPRECATED] Dreamweaver instructed us to bring it to Hibernal Hollow in the hopes that it may be saved.
[DEPRECATED] I only hope... that the hollow survives where my own grove did not.

Text: I was not always so. I joined the Wild Hunt only recently... after my grove had to be sacrificed to save the others.

Text1: My grove was lost as well... but not to the drought. We were overrun by masked fae. My friends...

Text: I am sorry, Niya. If only the Wild Hunt could have been there... but our numbers are stretched perilously thin.

Text1: As is the Winter Queen...

Text: She bears the greatest burden of us all. We must do what we can to share it.
[DEPRECATED] Hibernal Hollow... my grove was sacrificed so groves like this could survive.
Please, Aliothe. Help us end this spirit's nightmare!

Text1: Accept this portion of my power, mortal. Use it to alter your shape into one that the soul below will find more... welcoming.
But if they found a way to break free of its influence, perhaps they can aid us.
This mortal has not been long upon our path, but their strides have echoed throughout the halls of the Ascended.
In service to our cause, they have defended our temples against invasion.
On this day, we welcome them into our sacred covenant.
Together, we will restore peace and order to this realm. Glory to Bastion!
The trap is set. Now we lure Mor'Bitan to his doom.

Text: Master, our preparations are complete. We await your arrival.
Finally! The power our new baron promised shall now--
No! The ritual... it is ruined!

Text1: It is you who are the fool, Mor'Bitan.
And your folly has brought your demise.

Text: Wretched spy! Curse you and your fallen house!

Text1: For Akarek!
Help! Heartwood Grove is under attack!
Their anima will feed our victory.
Leave their husks to rot!

Text: Oh no...
Aliothe, look!
The wildseed... I no longer sense its dreams.

Text1: Unless we save her soon, she will be lost forever!
There are too many of them!

Text: Protect the heart at all costs!

Text1: Hmph! I can't leave you alone for a moment, can I?
Well, come along! We have work to do!

Text: Your infestation is at an end, monster!

Text1: Wait! I sense something... hidden from sight.
Ara'lon!

Text: A Drust trick to distract us from their true target!
Do you know where their leader has gone?
Awakening... she seeks... Awakening...
We will stop her, Ara'lon. I swear it. For Queen and grove.
For Queen... and grove...
Wild Hunt! We ride for the Grove of Awakening!

Text1: We're so sorry, Ara'lon. Night embrace you.

Text: Slay the mortal! Bring me that runeblade!
The foes of the worthy shall be vanquished.
Fall back!

Text1: The Seat of the Primus is ours!

Text: Allies, brace yourselves!

Text1: Long ago, we drew upon its magic to ensure the Maw would be inescapable. That the Banished One would remain forever bound.
Exposed the traitor Denathrius, and braved the terrors of the Maw itself.

Text: We can't fight our way in. There's too many of them.
This calls for a change of strategy.
Play dead. If they think you're a lifeless husk, they'll collect you for parts.
Go on. I'll create a diversion.
Face me, traitors! The House of Constructs will fall!
Capture that fool!
Text1: Capture that fool!

Text: The rest of you, scour the field. Bring me fuel for the Body Banks!
Text1: The rest of you, scour the field. Bring me fuel for the Body Banks!
I once said that your voice is but one bird singing in the night.
Well... I think it's time we all sang with you.

Text: Look at you. Pathetic. A puppet dancing on strings.
I will not break... I will not break... I will not...
Fool. Your mind is already broken.
But even a broken thing can be made to serve.
Countless secrets extracted. Insidious designs forged into weapons for my armies.
But I require... more.
(screams in pain)
Your grandest design... to claim the final prize.
The secret that the First Ones sought to hide.
Yes. Your finest mourneblade...
...and a crown fit for the king of the damned.
The vessels... of Domination.
Focus. Strategy. Relentlessness.
Enemies arise from without and within.
Might without control is wasted.
Duty is a mantle worn by all who serve.
Victory will be claimed not by a single house, but through the strength of our covenant.
For Maldraxxus!

Text1: Defenders of Maldraxxus! Through deceit and treachery, Kel'Thuzad has turned our great houses against one another.
He conspires with outside forces and defies the will of the Primus! Today he will answer for his crimes!
Oh, that worked? And the Maw Walker survived! Fantastic. Um... best not leave the Maw like that again. It may undo your existence.
Kel'Thuzad's puppets will be breach the outer wall soon. We should consider a retreat.

Text: Not yet. If we retreat, we lose more than merely this citadel.

Text1: Centurions! Advance! Destroy the intruders!

Text: Mephiles! You incompetent fool!
You are too late! The way opens!
That beast is incinerating our forces! We'll be overrun!

Text1: Necrolords, hold your ground! We will not fail Maldraxxus!

Text: Hail, baroness. Revendreth stands with you!

Text1: Raise your sword, champion! For Maldraxxus!

Text: Focus.
Dominate.
Fight always for the good of the realm.
Stand firm.
Defend the realms of Death.
These are the weapons of the Necrolords.
Destroy these meddlers!
Mevix will suffer for his defiance!
Text1: Mevix will suffer for his defiance!
You will never escape the Maw!
